VALUES(1676, '''Of the many fearsome beasts that roam our land, none is more deadly than the basilisk. Capable of living for hundreds of years, instant death awaits any who meet this giant serpent''s eye. Spiders flee before it.'' Ron, this is it. The monster in the Chamber of Secrets is a basilisk. That''s why I can hear it speak. It''s a snake!', 62, 1, 43);
