VALUES(2022, 'Thanks, Ron.', 76, 1, 42);
VALUES(2023, 'Why are we stopping? We can''t be there yet.', 76, 3, 42);
VALUES(2024, 'What''s going on?', 76, 2, 42);
VALUES(2025, 'I don''t know. Maybe we''ve broken down.', 76, 1, 42);
VALUES(2026, 'Ouch, Ron. That was my foot.', 76, 3, 42);
VALUES(2027, 'There''s something moving out there. I think... someone''s coming aboard.', 76, 2, 42);
VALUES(2028, 'Bloody hell! What''s happening?', 76, 2, 42);
VALUES(2029, 'Harry. Harry, are you all right?', 76, 3, 42);
VALUES(2030, 'Thank you.', 76, 1, 42);
VALUES(2031, 'Here, eat this. It''ll help. It''s all right. It''s chocolate.', 76, 11, 42);
VALUES(2032, 'What was that thing that came?', 76, 1, 42);
VALUES(2033, 'It was a dementor. One of the guards of Azkaban. It''s gone now. It was searching the train for Sirius Black. If you''ll excuse me, I need to have a little word with the driver. Eat. You''ll feel better.', 76, 11, 42);
VALUES(2034, 'What happened to me?', 76, 1, 42);
VALUES(2035, 'Well, you sort of went rigid. We thought maybe you were having a fit or something.', 76, 2, 42);
VALUES(2036, 'And did either of you two... you know... pass out?', 76, 1, 42);
VALUES(2037, 'No. I felt weird, though. Like I''d never be cheerful again.', 76, 2, 42);
VALUES(2038, 'But someone was screaming. A woman.', 76, 1, 42);
VALUES(2039, 'No one was screaming, Harry.', 76, 3, 42);
VALUES(2454, 'On the slope... Ah, Hagrid.', 91, 4, 40);
VALUES(2040, 'Welcome! Welcome to another year at Hogwarts! Now, I''d like to say a few words... before we all become too befuddled by our excellent feast. First, I''m pleased to welcome Professor R.J. Lupin... who''s kindly consented to fill the post... of Defense Against the Dark Arts teacher. Good luck, Professor.', 77, 4, 36);
VALUES(2041, 'Of course. That''s why he knew to give you the chocolate, Harry.', 77, 3, 36);
VALUES(2042, 'Potter. Is it true you fainted? I mean, you actually fainted?', 77, 12, 36);
VALUES(2043, 'Shove off, Malfoy.', 77, 2, 36);
VALUES(2044, 'How did he find out?', 77, 1, 36);
VALUES(2045, 'Just forget it.', 77, 3, 36);
VALUES(2046, 'Our Care of Magical Creatures teacher... has decided to retire... in order to spend more time with his remaining limbs. Fortunately, I''m delighted to announce... that his place will be taken by none other... than our own Rubeus Hagrid. Finally, on a more disquieting note... at the request of the Ministry of Magic... Hogwarts will, until further notice, play host to the dementors of Azkaban... until such a time as Sirius Black is captured. The dementors will be stationed at every entrance to the grounds. Now whilst I''ve been assured... that their presence will not disrupt our day-to-day activities... a word of caution. Dementors are vicious creatures. They''ll not distinguish... between the one they hunt and the one who gets in their way. Therefore, I must warn each and every one of you... to give them no reason to harm you. It is not in the nature of a dementor to be forgiving. But you know, happiness can be found... even in the darkest of times... if one only remembers to turn on the light.', 77, 4, 36);
VALUES(2047, 'Fortuna Major. Here, listen. She just won''t let me in. Fortuna Major.', 77, 29, 39);
VALUES(2048, 'No, no, no. Wait, wait. Watch this. Oh, amazing! Just with my voice.', 77, 141, 39);
VALUES(2049, 'Fortuna Major.', 77, 1, 39);
VALUES(2050, 'Yes, all right. Go in.', 77, 141, 39);
VALUES(2051, 'Thank you.', 77, 1, 39);
VALUES(2052, 'She''s still doing that after three years. She can''t even sing. Exactly. Hey, man. Hey, man. Oh, God. That''s awful.', 77, 1, 39);
VALUES(2053, 'She''s still doing that after three years. She can''t even sing. Exactly. Hey, man. Hey, man. Oh, God. That''s awful.', 77, 29, 39);
VALUES(2054, '. Green. That''s a monkey. What is that? You call that a monkey? Do not give him one again. Hey, Neville, try an elephant.', 77, 2, 39);
VALUES(2055, 'Ron, catch.', 77, 29, 39);
VALUES(2056, 'I will.', 77, 2, 39);
VALUES(2057, 'I think we have a winner.', 77, 29, 39);
VALUES(2058, 'Oh, don''t try one of them. Oh, no. Look at him. His face.', 77, 2, 39);
VALUES(2059, 'Welcome, my children. In this room, you shall explore the noble art of Divination. In this room, you shall discover if you possess the Sight. Hello. I am Professor Trelawney. Together we shall cast ourselves into the future. This term, we''ll focus on Tasseomancy, the art of reading tea leaves. So please, take the cup of the person sitting opposite you. What do you see? The truth lies buried like a sentence deep within a book, waiting to be read. But first, you must broaden your minds. First, you must look beyond.', 78, 38, 32);
VALUES(2060, 'What a load of rubbish.', 78, 3, 32);
VALUES(2061, 'Where did you come from?', 78, 2, 32);
VALUES(2062, 'Me? I''ve been here all this time.', 78, 3, 32);
VALUES(2063, 'You, boy... Is your grandmother quite well?', 78, 38, 32);
VALUES(2064, 'I think so.', 78, 10, 32);
VALUES(2065, 'I wouldn''t be so sure of that. Give me the cup. Pity. Broaden your minds. Your aura is pulsing, dear. Are you in the beyond? I think you are.', 78, 38, 32);
VALUES(2066, 'Sure.', 78, 2, 32);
VALUES(2067, 'Look at the cup. Tell me what you see.', 78, 38, 32);
VALUES(2068, 'Oh, yeah. Um... Well, Harry''s got sort of a wonky cross. That''s trials and suffering. And that there could be the sun and that''s happiness. So... you''re gonna suffer, but you''re gonna be... happy about it.', 78, 2, 32);
VALUES(2069, 'Give me the cup. Oh, my dear boy. My dear... you have the Grim.', 78, 38, 32);
VALUES(2070, 'The Grin? What''s the Grin? Not the Grin, you idiot. The Grim. Taking form of a giant spectral dog. It''s among the darkest omens in our world. It''s an omen... of death.', 78, 126, 32);
VALUES(2071, 'You don''t think that Grim thing''s got anything to do with Sirius Black?', 78, 2, 40);
VALUES(2072, 'Oh, honestly, Ron. If you ask me, Divination''s a woolly discipline. Now, Ancient Runes, that''s a fascinating subject.', 78, 3, 40);
VALUES(2073, 'Ancient Runes? Exactly how many classes are you taking?', 78, 2, 40);
VALUES(2074, 'A fair few.', 78, 3, 40);
VALUES(2075, 'Hang on. That''s not possible. Ancient Runes is in the same time as Divination. You have to be in two classes at once.', 78, 2, 40);
VALUES(2076, 'Don''t be silly Ron. How could anyone be in two classes at once? Broaden your minds. Use your Inner Eye to see the future!.', 78, 3, 40);
VALUES(2077, 'That''s it. Come on, now. Come closer. Less talking, if you don''t mind. I got a real treat for you today. A great lesson. So follow me. Right, you lot. Less chattering. Form a group over there. And open your books to page 49.', 79, 5, 40);
VALUES(2078, 'Exactly how do we do that?', 79, 12, 40);
VALUES(2079, 'Just stroke the spine, of course. Goodness me.', 79, 5, 40);
VALUES(2080, 'Don''t be such a wimp, Longbottom.', 79, 12, 40);
VALUES(2081, 'I''m okay. Okay.', 79, 10, 40);
VALUES(2082, 'I think they''re funny.', 79, 3, 40);
VALUES(2083, 'Oh, yeah. Terribly funny. Really Witty. God, this place has gone to the dogs. Wait until Father hears Dumbledore''s got this oaf teaching classes.', 79, 12, 40);
VALUES(2084, 'Shut up, Malfoy.', 79, 1, 40);
VALUES(2085, 'D-Dementor! Dementor!', 79, 12, 40);
VALUES(2086, 'Just ignore him.', 79, 3, 40);
VALUES(2087, 'You''re supposed to stroke it.', 79, 2, 40);
VALUES(2088, 'Yeah.', 79, 10, 40);
VALUES(2089, 'Isn''t he beautiful? Say hello to Buckbeak.', 79, 5, 40);
VALUES(2090, 'Hagrid, exactly what is that?', 79, 2, 40);
VALUES(2091, 'That, Ron, is a hippogriff. First thing you wanna know about hippogriffs is that they''re very proud creatures. Very easily offended. You do not want to insult a hippogriff. It may just be the last thing you ever do. Now, who''d like to come and say hello? Well done, Harry. Well done. Come on now. Now... you have to let him make the first move. It''s only polite. So... step up. Give him a nice bow. Then you wait and see if he bows back. If he does, you can go and touch him. If not... Well, we''ll get to that later. Just make your bow. Nice and low. Back off, Harry. Back off. Keep still. Keep still. Well done, Harry. Well done. Here, you big brute, you. Right. I think you can go and pat him now. Go on. Don''t be shy. Nice and slow, now. Nice and slow. Slow. Not so fast, Harry. Slow down, Harry. That''s it... Nice and slow. Now let him come to you. Slowly, now, slowly, slowly... That''s it... Yes! Well done! Well done, Harry, well done! I think he may let you ride him now.', 79, 5, 40);
VALUES(2092, 'What?', 79, 1, 40);
VALUES(2095, 'Put you over here, just behind the wing joint. Don''t pull out any of his feathers, because he won''t thank you for that. Well done, Harry, and well done, Buckbeak.', 79, 5, 40);
VALUES(2096, 'That was wicked, Harry!', 79, 2, 40);
VALUES(2097, 'Oh, please.', 79, 12, 40);
VALUES(2098, 'Well done, well done. How am I doing me first day?', 79, 5, 40);
VALUES(2099, 'Brilliant, professor.', 79, 1, 40);
VALUES(2100, 'Yes you''re not dangerous at all, are you, you great ugly brute!', 79, 12, 40);
VALUES(2101, 'Malfoy, no... No! Buckbeak! Whoa, whoa, whoa... Whoa! Buckbeak! Away, you silly creature!', 79, 5, 40);
VALUES(2102, 'It''s killed me! It''s killed me!', 79, 12, 40);
VALUES(2103, 'Calm down! It''s just a scratch!', 79, 5, 40);
VALUES(2104, 'Hagrid! He has to be taken to the hospital.', 79, 3, 40);
VALUES(2105, 'I''m the teacher. I''ll do it.', 79, 5, 40);
VALUES(2106, 'Oh You''re gonna regret this.', 79, 12, 40);
VALUES(2107, 'Class dismissed!', 79, 5, 40);
VALUES(2108, 'You and your bloody chicken!', 79, 12, 40);
VALUES(2109, 'Does it hurt terribly, Draco?', 80, 91, 36);
VALUES(2110, 'It comes and it goes. Still, I consider myself lucky. Madam Pomfrey said another minute and I could''ve lost my arm. I couldn''t do homework for weeks.', 80, 12, 36);
VALUES(2111, 'Listen to the idiot. He''s really laying it on thick, isn''t he?', 80, 2, 36);
VALUES(2112, 'At least Hagrid didn''t get fired.', 80, 1, 36);
VALUES(2113, 'Yeah but I heard Draco''s father''s furious. We haven''t heard the end of this.', 80, 3, 36);
VALUES(2114, 'He''s been sighted! He''s been sighted!', 80, 29, 36);
VALUES(2115, 'Who?', 80, 2, 36);
VALUES(2116, 'Sirius Black!', 80, 29, 36);
VALUES(2117, 'Dufftown? That''s not far from here.', 80, 3, 36);
VALUES(2118, 'You don''t think he''d come to Hogwarts, do you? With dementors at every entrance?', 80, 126, 36);
VALUES(2119, 'Dementors? He''s already slipped past them once. Who''s to say he won''t do it again?', 80, 29, 36);
VALUES(2120, 'That''s right. Black could be anywhere. It''s like trying to catch smoke. Like trying to catch smoke with your bare hands.', 80, 126, 36);
VALUES(2121, 'Intriguing, isn''t it? Would anyone like to venture a guess... as to what is inside?', 80, 11, 30);
VALUES(2122, 'That''s a boggart, that is.', 80, 75, 30);
VALUES(2123, 'Very good, Mr. Thomas. Now, can anybody tell me what a boggart looks like?', 80, 11, 30);
VALUES(2124, 'No one knows.', 80, 3, 30);
VALUES(2125, 'When did she get here?', 80, 2, 30);
VALUES(2126, 'Boggarts are shape-shifters. They take the shape of whatever a particular person fears the most. That''s what makes them so...', 80, 3, 30);
VALUES(2127, 'So terrifying, yes, yes, yes... Luckily, a very simple charm exists to repel a boggart. Let''s practice it now. Without wands, please. After me. Riddikulus!', 80, 11, 30);
VALUES(2128, 'Riddikulus!', 80, 136, 30);
VALUES(2129, 'Very good. A little louder and very clear. Listen: Riddikulus!', 80, 11, 30);
VALUES(2130, 'Riddikulus!', 80, 136, 30);
VALUES(2131, 'This class is ridiculous.', 80, 12, 30);
VALUES(2132, 'Very good. So much for the easy part. You see, the incantation alone is not enough. What really finishes a boggart is laughter. You need to force it to assume a shape you find truly amusing. Let me explain. Uh... Neville, would you join me, please? Come on, don''t be shy. Come on. Come on. Hello. Neville, what frightens you most of all?', 80, 11, 30);
VALUES(2133, 'Professor Snape.', 80, 10, 30);
VALUES(2134, 'Sorry?', 80, 11, 30);
VALUES(2135, 'Professor Snape.', 80, 10, 30);
VALUES(2136, 'Professor Snape. Yes, frightens all. And I believe you live with your grandmother.', 80, 11, 30);
VALUES(2137, 'Y-Yes but I don''t want that boggart to turn into her, either.', 80, 10, 30);
VALUES(2138, 'No... it won''t. I want you to picture her clothes. Only her clothes, very clearly, in your mind.', 80, 11, 30);
VALUES(2139, 'She carries a red handbag...', 80, 10, 30);
VALUES(2140, 'We don''t need to hear. As long as you see it, we''ll see it. Now, when I open that wardrobe... here''s what I want you to do. Excuse me. Imagine Professor Snape in your grandmother''s clothes. Can you do that? Yes. Wand at the ready. One, two, three. Think, Neville, think.', 80, 11, 30);
VALUES(2141, 'Riddikulus!', 80, 10, 30);
VALUES(2142, 'Wonderful, Neville, wonderful! Incredible! Okay... to the back, Neville. Everyone, form a line! Form a line! I want everyone to picture the thing they fear the very most... and turn it into something funny. Next! Ron! Concentrate. Face your fear. Be brave! Wand at the ready, Ron, wand at the ready.', 80, 11, 30);
VALUES(2143, 'Riddikulus!', 80, 2, 30);
VALUES(2144, 'Yes! You see? Very good, very good! Marvelous! Absolutely, very, very enjoyable! Parvati! Next! Show us what you see. Keep your nerve. Steady.', 80, 11, 30);
VALUES(2145, 'Riddikulus!', 80, 78, 30);
VALUES(2146, 'And next! Step up, step up! Wonderful, wonderful! Here! Riddikulus! Right. Sorry about that. That''s enough for today. Collect your books from the back. That''s the end of the lesson. Thank you! Sorry! Sorry, you can have too much of a good thing.', 80, 11, 30);
VALUES(2147, 'Now remember, these visits to Hogsmeade village are a privilege. Should your behavior reflect poorly on the school in anyway that privilege shall not be extended again. No permission form signed, no visiting the village. That''s the rule, Potter.', 81, 7, 27);
VALUES(2148, 'Those with permission, follow me. Those without, stay put.', 81, 35, 27);
VALUES(2149, 'But professor I thought if you signed it, then I could...', 81, 1, 27);
VALUES(2150, 'I can''t. Only a parent or a guardian can sign. Since I am neither, it would be inappropriate. I''m sorry, Potter. That''s my final word.', 81, 7, 27);
VALUES(2151, 'Forget about it, guys. See you later.', 81, 1, 27);
VALUES(2152, 'Professor, can I ask you something?', 81, 1, 29);
VALUES(2153, 'You want to know why I stopped you facing that boggart, yes? I would''ve thought it''d be obvious. I assumed it would take the shape of Lord Voldemort.', 81, 11, 29);
VALUES(2154, 'I did think of Voldemort at first. But then I remembered that night on the train... and the dementor.', 81, 1, 29);
VALUES(2155, 'I''m very impressed. That suggests what you fear the most is fear itself. This is very wise.', 81, 11, 29);
VALUES(2156, 'Before I fainted... I heard something. A woman... screaming.', 81, 1, 29);
VALUES(2157, 'Dementors force us to relive our very worst memories. Our pain becomes their power.', 81, 11, 29);
VALUES(2158, 'I think it was my mother... the night she was murdered.', 81, 1, 29);
VALUES(2223, 'I''m sorry to hear about your broomstick. Is there no chance of fixing it?', 84, 11, 37);
VALUES(2224, 'No. Professor, why do the dementors affect me so? I mean, more than everyone else?', 84, 1, 37);
VALUES(2455, 'Professor Dumbledore.', 91, 5, 40);
VALUES(2159, 'The very first time I saw you, Harry, I recognized you immediately. Not by your scar, by your eyes. They''re your mother, Lily''s. Yes. Oh, yes. I knew her. Your mother was there for me at a time when no one else was. Not only was she a singularly gifted witch... she was also an uncommonly kind woman. She had a way of seeing the beauty in others... even, and perhaps most especially, when that person could not see it in themselves. And your father, James, on the other hand... he... He had a certain, shall we say, talent for trouble. A talent, rumor has it, he passed on to you. You''re more like them than you know, Harry. In time, you''ll come to see just how much.', 81, 11, 29);
VALUES(2160, 'Honeyduke''s Sweetshop is brilliant, but nothing beats Zonko''s Joke Shop. We never did got a chance to go to the Shrieking Shack though. You heard it''s the most...', 82, 2, 39);
VALUES(2161, 'The most haunted building in Britain. Yeah I know. What''s going on?', 82, 1, 39);
VALUES(2162, 'Probably Neville forgotten the password again.', 82, 2, 39);
VALUES(2163, 'Hey!.', 82, 10, 39);
VALUES(2164, 'Oh, you''re there.', 82, 2, 39);
VALUES(2165, 'Let me through, please. Excuse me! I''m Head Boy! Get back, all of you. No one is to enter this dormitory until it''s been searched.', 82, 37, 39);
VALUES(2166, 'The Fat Lady! She''s gone!', 82, 20, 39);
VALUES(2167, 'Serves her right. She was a terrible singer.', 82, 2, 39);
VALUES(2168, 'It''s not funny, Ron.', 82, 3, 39);
VALUES(2169, 'Keep calm, everyone. Break into fours. Back to your common room. Be quiet.', 82, 37, 39);
VALUES(2170, 'Make way.', 82, 4, 39);
VALUES(2171, 'The headmaster''s here.', 82, 37, 39);
VALUES(2172, 'Come on, move.', 82, 4, 39);
VALUES(2173, 'You heard. Move!', 82, 37, 39);
VALUES(2174, 'Mr. Filch? Round up the ghosts. Tell them to search every painting in the castle to find the Fat Lady.', 82, 4, 39);
VALUES(2175, 'There''s no need for ghosts, professor. The Fat Lady''s there.', 82, 35, 39);
VALUES(2176, 'Mind where you''re going! Slow down! You listen! I''m Head Boy! Come back here!', 82, 37, 39);
VALUES(2177, 'Keep moving!', 82, 4, 39);
VALUES(2178, 'Dear lady, who did this to you?', 82, 4, 39);
VALUES(2179, 'Eyes like the devil, he''s got, and a soul as dark as his name. It''s him, headmaster. The one they all talk about. He''s here, somewhere in the castle! Sirius Black!', 82, 141, 39);
VALUES(2180, 'Secure the castle, Mr. Filch. The rest of you, to the Great Hall.', 82, 4, 39);
VALUES(2181, 'I''ve searched the Astronomy Tower and the Owlery, sir. But there''s nothing there.', 82, 35, 36);
VALUES(2182, 'Ah, thank you.', 82, 4, 36);
VALUES(2183, 'The third floor''s clear too, sir.', 82, 59, 36);
VALUES(2184, 'Very good.', 82, 4, 36);
VALUES(2185, 'I''ve done the dungeons, headmaster. No sign of Black, nor anywhere else in the castle.', 82, 6, 36);
VALUES(2186, 'I didn''t really expect him to linger.', 82, 4, 36);
VALUES(2187, 'Remarkable feat, don''t you think? To enter Hogwarts Castle on one''s own... completely undetected?', 82, 6, 36);
VALUES(2188, 'Quite remarkable, yes.', 82, 4, 36);
VALUES(2189, 'Any theories on how he managed it?', 82, 6, 36);
VALUES(2190, 'Many. Each as unlikely as the next.', 82, 4, 36);
VALUES(2191, 'You may recall... prior to the start of term I expressed concerns... about your appointment of Professor...', 82, 6, 36);
VALUES(2192, 'Not a single professor inside this castle would help Sirius Black enter it. I''m quite convinced the castle is safe... and I''m more than willing to send the students back to their houses.', 82, 4, 36);
VALUES(2193, 'What about Potter? Should he be warned?', 82, 6, 36);
VALUES(2194, 'Perhaps. But for now, let him sleep. For in dreams, we enter a world that''s entirely our own. Let them swim in the deepest ocean or glide over the highest cloud.', 82, 4, 36);
VALUES(2195, 'Turn to page 394.', 83, 6, 30);
VALUES(2196, 'Excuse me, sir. Where''s Professor Lupin?', 83, 1, 30);
VALUES(2197, 'That''s not really your concern, is it, Potter? Suffice it to say your professor finds himself incapable of teaching... at the present time. Turn to page 394.', 83, 6, 30);
VALUES(2198, 'Werewolves?', 83, 2, 30);
VALUES(2199, 'But sir, we just learned about red caps and hinkypunks. We''re not meant to start that for weeks.', 83, 3, 30);
VALUES(2200, 'Quiet.', 83, 6, 30);
VALUES(2201, 'When did she come in? Did you see her come in?', 83, 2, 30);
VALUES(2202, 'Now, which one of you can tell me the difference... between an Animagus and a werewolf? No one? How disappointing.', 83, 6, 30);
VALUES(2203, 'Please, sir. An Animagus is a wizard who elects to turn into an animal. A werewolf has no choice. With each full moon, when he transforms, he no longer remembers who he is. He''d kill his best friend if he crossed his path. Furthermore, the werewolf only responds to the call of its own kind.', 83, 3, 30);
VALUES(2204, 'Thank you, Mr. Malfoy. That''s the second time... you''ve spoken out of turn, Miss Granger. Are you incapable of restraining yourself... or do you take pride in being an insufferable know-it-all?', 83, 6, 30);
VALUES(2205, 'He''s got a point, you know.', 83, 2, 30);
VALUES(2206, 'Five points from Gryffindor. As an antidote to your ignorance, and on my desk, by Monday morning... two rolls of parchment on the werewolf, with emphasis... on recognizing it.', 83, 6, 30);
VALUES(2207, 'Sir, it''s Quidditch tomorrow.', 83, 1, 30);
VALUES(2208, 'Then I suggest you take extra care, Mr. Potter. Loss of limb will not excuse you. Page 394. The term werewolf... is a contraction of the Anglo-Saxon word were... which means man, and wolf. Werewolf, man-wolf. There are several ways to become a werewolf. They include being given the power of shape-shifting... being bitten by a werewolf...', 83, 6, 30);
VALUES(2209, 'Go, Harry! Go, Harry!', 84, 3, 51);
VALUES(2210, 'Arresto momentum!', 84, 4, 51);
VALUES(2211, 'He looks a bit peaky, doesn''t he?', 84, 2, 43);
VALUES(2212, 'Peaky? What do you expect? He fell over 100 feet.', 84, 14, 43);
VALUES(2213, 'Yeah, come on Ron, let''s walk you off the astronomy tower and see what you look like.', 84, 19, 43);
VALUES(2214, 'Probably a right sight better than he normally does.', 84, 1, 43);
VALUES(2215, 'How are you feeling?', 84, 3, 43);
VALUES(2216, 'Oh, brilliant.', 84, 1, 43);
VALUES(2217, 'You gave us a right good scare there, mate.', 84, 14, 43);
VALUES(2218, 'What happened?', 84, 1, 43);
VALUES(2219, 'Well, you fell off your broom.', 84, 2, 43);
VALUES(2220, 'Really? I meant the match. Who won?', 84, 1, 43);
VALUES(2221, 'Umm... no one blames you, Harry. The dementors aren''t supposed to come inside the grounds. Dumbledore''s furious. As soon as he saved you, he sent them off.', 84, 3, 43);
VALUES(2222, 'There''s something else you should know too. When you fell, your broom sort of blew into the Whomping Willow, and... Well...', 84, 2, 43);
VALUES(2225, 'Listen. Dementors are amongst the foulest creatures to walk this earth. They feed on every good feeling, every happy memory... until a person is left with absolutely nothing but his worst experiences. You are not weak, Harry. The dementors affect you most because there are true horrors in your past. Horrors your classmates can scarcely imagine. You have nothing to be ashamed of.', 84, 11, 37);
VALUES(2226, 'I''m scared, professor.', 84, 1, 37);
VALUES(2227, 'Well I''d consider you a fool if you weren''t.', 84, 11, 37);
VALUES(2228, 'I need to know how to fight them. You could teach me. You made that dementor on the train go away.', 84, 1, 37);
VALUES(2229, 'There was only one that night.', 84, 11, 37);
VALUES(2230, 'But you made it go away.', 84, 1, 37);
VALUES(2231, 'I don''t pretend to be an expert, Harry. But as the dementors seem to have developed a particular interest in you... perhaps I should teach you. But after the holidays. For now, I need to rest.', 84, 11, 37);
VALUES(2232, 'Last call for Hogsmeade! Come on, now!', 85, 35, 27);
VALUES(2233, 'Guys, let me go.', 85, 1, 27);
VALUES(2234, 'Clever, Harry.', 85, 14, 27);
VALUES(2235, 'But not clever enough. Besides, we''ve got a better way.', 85, 19, 27);
VALUES(2236, 'I''m trying to get to Hogsmeade.', 85, 1, 27);
VALUES(2237, 'We know. Don''t worry. We''ll get you there. We''ll show you a quicker way. If you pipe down.', 85, 14, 27);
VALUES(2238, 'We know. Don''t worry. We''ll get you there. We''ll show you a quicker way. If you pipe down.', 85, 19, 27);
VALUES(2239, 'Oh. Bless him.', 85, 14, 27);
