VALUES(2289, 'Get out of the way! Move!', 86, 12, 19);
VALUES(2290, 'Malfoy! Wait! Wait!', 86, 80, 19);
VALUES(2291, 'Harry!', 86, 3, 19);
VALUES(2292, 'Bloody hell, Harry. That was not funny.', 86, 2, 19);
VALUES(2293, 'Those weasels! Never told me about any Marauder''s Map.', 87, 2, 22);
VALUES(2294, 'But Harry isn''t going to keep it. He''s going to turn it over to Professor McGonagall. Aren''t you?', 87, 3, 22);
VALUES(2295, 'Sure. Along with his Invisibility Cloak.', 87, 2, 22);
VALUES(2296, 'Oh, Look who it is. Madam Rosmerta. Ron fancies her.', 87, 3, 22);
VALUES(2297, 'That''s not true!', 87, 2, 22);
VALUES(2298, 'Professor McGonagall!', 87, 17, 22);
VALUES(2299, 'Cornelius!', 87, 7, 22);
VALUES(2300, 'Allow me, minister.', 87, 5, 22);
VALUES(2301, 'Oh, Hagrid...', 87, 17, 22);
VALUES(2302, 'Sorry about that.', 87, 5, 22);
VALUES(2303, 'Rosmerta, my dear. I hope business is good.', 87, 17, 22);
VALUES(2304, 'It''d be a lot better if the Ministry wasn''t sending dementors... into my pub every other night!', 87, 66, 22);
VALUES(2305, 'We have... We have a killer on the loose!', 87, 17, 22);
VALUES(2306, 'Sirius Black in Hogsmeade! And what would bring him here?', 87, 66, 22);
VALUES(2307, 'Harry Potter.', 87, 17, 22);
VALUES(2308, 'Harry Potter?', 87, 66, 22);
VALUES(2309, 'Come.', 87, 17, 22);
VALUES(2310, 'Harry!', 87, 3, 22);
VALUES(2311, 'No underage wizards allowed in today! Shut the damn door!', 87, 133, 22);
VALUES(2312, 'So rude.', 87, 3, 22);
VALUES(2313, 'Thick heads.', 87, 2, 22);
VALUES(2382, 'Yes, we are.', 89, 137, 28);
VALUES(2314, 'Thick heads?! How dare they! Who are they calling thick heads? Young whippersnappers!', 87, 133, 22);
VALUES(2315, 'Nobody''s going to come to a pub where they''re gonna get scared out of their wits. Why?', 87, 66, 22);
VALUES(2316, 'Professor Dumbledore does not want dementors around the place, I can assure you.', 87, 7, 22);
VALUES(2317, 'Now, tell me what this is all about.', 87, 66, 22);
VALUES(2318, 'Well. Now years ago, when Harry Potter''s parents realized they were marked for death... You remember? They went into hiding. Few knew where they were. One who did was Sirius Black. And he told You-Know-Who!', 87, 7, 22);
VALUES(2319, 'Not only did Black lead You-Know-Who to the Potters that night, but he also killed one of their friends, Peter Pettigrew!', 87, 17, 22);
VALUES(2320, 'Peter Pettigrew?', 87, 66, 22);
VALUES(2321, 'Yes, little lump of a boy. Always trailing after Sirius Black.', 87, 7, 22);
VALUES(2322, 'Ah, I remember him. Never let James and Sirius out of his sight. But what happened?', 87, 66, 22);
VALUES(2323, 'Well Peter Pettigrew tried to warn the Potters... and might have managed to, had he not run into an old friend, Sirius Black.', 87, 7, 22);
VALUES(2324, 'Black was vicious. He didn''t kill Pettigrew. He destroyed him! A finger. That''s all that was left. A finger. Nothing else.', 87, 17, 22);
VALUES(2325, 'Yes. Sirius Black may not have put his hands to the Potters, but he''s the reason they''re dead.', 87, 7, 22);
VALUES(2326, 'And now he wants to finish what he started.', 87, 17, 22);
VALUES(2327, 'Mhmm.', 87, 7, 22);
VALUES(2328, 'I don''t believe it.', 87, 66, 22);
VALUES(2329, 'Ah, that''s not the worst of it.', 87, 17, 22);
VALUES(2330, 'What could be worse?', 87, 66, 22);
VALUES(2331, 'This: Sirius Black was... and remains to this day... Harry Potter''s godfather!', 87, 7, 22);
VALUES(2332, 'Ron, look! Sorry, sorry. Excuse me, excuse me, sorry. Harry, what happened?', 87, 3, 22);
VALUES(2333, 'He was their friend... and he betrayed them. He was their friend! I hope he finds me. Because when he does, I''m gonna be ready! When he does, I''m gonna kill him!', 87, 1, 22);
VALUES(2334, 'Harry. There you are. You came. Are you sure about this, Harry? You know this is very advanced magic well beyond the Ordinary Wizarding Level.', 88, 11, 30);
VALUES(2335, 'I''m sure.', 88, 1, 30);
VALUES(2336, 'Well, everything''s prepared. Now, the spell I''m going to try to teach you is called the Patronus Charm. Did you ever hear of it? No? Well... A Patronus is a kind of positive force. For the wizard who conjures one... it works something like a shield, with the dementor feeding on it rather than him. But in order for it to work, you need to think of a memory. Not just any memory, a very happy memory, a very powerful memory.', 88, 11, 30);
VALUES(2337, 'Can you do this? Yes. Very well. Close your eyes. Concentrate. Explore your past. Do you have a memory? Allow it to fill you up. Lose yourself within it. Then speak the incantation, Expecto Patronum.', 88, 11, 30);
VALUES(2338, 'Expecto Patronum.', 88, 1, 30);
VALUES(2339, 'Very good. Shall we? Wand at the ready.', 88, 11, 30);
VALUES(2340, 'Expecto Patronum! Expecto... Expecto... Expect...', 88, 1, 30);
VALUES(2341, 'Here we go. Come on. Sit up. Deep breaths. It''s all right. I didn''t expect you to do it the first time. That would have been remarkable. Here, eat this. You''ll feel better.', 88, 11, 30);
VALUES(2342, 'That''s one nasty dementor.', 88, 1, 30);
VALUES(2343, 'Oh, no, no, no. That was a boggart, Harry. A boggart. The real thing would be worse. Much, much worse. As a matter of interest, what were you thinking? Which memory did you choose?', 88, 11, 30);
VALUES(2344, 'The first time I rode a broom.', 88, 1, 30);
VALUES(2345, 'That''s not good enough. Not nearly good enough.', 88, 11, 30);
VALUES(2346, 'There''s another. It''s not... happy, exactly. Well, it is. It''s the happiest I''ve ever felt... but it''s complicated.', 88, 1, 30);
VALUES(2347, 'Is it strong? Then let''s give it a try. You feel ready?', 88, 11, 30);
VALUES(2348, 'Just do it. Expecto Patronum! Expecto Patronum!', 88, 1, 30);
VALUES(2349, 'Yes! Well done, Harry. Well done!', 88, 11, 30);
VALUES(2350, 'I think I''ve had enough for today.', 88, 1, 30);
VALUES(2351, 'Yes. Sit down. Here. Eat this, it helps. It really helps. And just so you know, Harry... I think you''d have given your father a run for his money. And that... is saying something.', 88, 11, 30);
VALUES(2352, 'I was thinking of him. And Mom. Seeing their faces. They were talking to me. Just talking. That''s the memory I chose. I don''t even know if it''s real. But it''s the best I have.', 88, 1, 30);
VALUES(2353, 'Beautiful day.', 88, 3, 37);
VALUES(2354, 'Gorgeous.', 88, 2, 37);
VALUES(2355, 'Unless of course you''ve been ripped to pieces!', 88, 2, 37);
