VALUES(2494, 'Expelliarmus! Well, well, Sirius. Looking rather ragged, aren''t we? Finally, the flesh reflects the madness within.', 93, 11, 20);
VALUES(2495, 'Well, you''d know all about the madness within, wouldn''t you Remus? I found him.', 93, 18, 20);
VALUES(2496, 'I know.', 93, 11, 20);
VALUES(2497, 'It''s him.', 93, 18, 20);
VALUES(2498, 'I understand.', 93, 11, 20);
VALUES(2499, 'Let''s kill him!', 93, 18, 20);
VALUES(2500, 'No! I trusted you! And all this time, you''ve been his friend. He''s a werewolf! That''s why he''s been missing classes.', 93, 3, 20);
VALUES(2501, 'How long have you known?', 93, 11, 20);
VALUES(2502, 'Since Professor Snape set the essay.', 93, 3, 20);
VALUES(2503, 'Well, well, well, Hermione. You really are the brightest witch of your age, I''ve ever met.', 93, 11, 20);
VALUES(2504, 'Enough talk, Remus! Come on, let''s kill him!', 93, 18, 20);
VALUES(2505, 'Wait!', 93, 11, 20);
VALUES(2506, 'I did my waiting! Twelve years of it! In Azkaban!', 93, 18, 20);
VALUES(2507, 'Very well. Kill him. But wait one more minute. Harry has the right to know why.', 93, 11, 20);
VALUES(2508, 'I know why. You betrayed my parents. You''re the reason they''re dead!', 93, 1, 20);
VALUES(2509, 'No, Harry it wasn''t him. Somebody did betray your parents... but it was somebody who, until quite recently, I believed to be dead!', 93, 11, 20);
VALUES(2510, 'Who was it, then?', 93, 1, 20);
VALUES(2511, 'Peter Pettigrew! And he''s in this room! Right now! Come out, come out, Peter! Come out, come out and play!', 94, 18, 20);
VALUES(2512, 'Expelliarmus! Vengeance is sweet. How I hoped I''d be the one to catch you.', 94, 6, 20);
VALUES(2513, 'Severus...', 94, 18, 20);
VALUES(2514, 'I told Dumbledore you were helping an old friend into the castle, and now here''s the proof.', 94, 6, 20);
VALUES(2515, 'Brilliant, Snape. Once again you''ve put your keen penetrating mind to the task and as usual come to the wrong conclusion. Now, if you''ll excuse us, Remus and I have some unfinished business... to attend to.', 94, 18, 20);
VALUES(2516, 'Give me a reason. I beg you!', 94, 6, 20);
VALUES(2517, 'Severus don''t be a fool.', 94, 11, 20);
VALUES(2518, 'He can''t help it. It''s habit.', 94, 18, 20);
VALUES(2519, 'Sirius be quiet.', 94, 11, 20);
VALUES(2520, 'Be quiet yourself Remus!', 94, 18, 20);
VALUES(2521, 'Oh listen to you two, quarreling like an old married couple.', 94, 6, 20);
VALUES(2522, 'Why don''t you run along and play with your chemistry set!', 94, 18, 20);
VALUES(2523, 'I could do it, you know. But why deny the dementors? They''re so longing to see you. Do I detect a flicker of fear? Oh, yes. A Dementor''s Kiss. One can only imagine what that must be like. It''s said to be nearly unbearable to witness, but I''ll do my best.', 94, 6, 20);
VALUES(2524, 'Severus, please.', 94, 11, 20);
VALUES(2525, 'After you.', 94, 6, 20);
VALUES(2526, 'Expelliarmus!', 94, 1, 20);
VALUES(2527, 'Harry! What did you just do?', 94, 2, 20);
VALUES(2528, 'You attacked a teacher!', 94, 3, 20);
VALUES(2529, 'Tell me about Peter.', 94, 1, 20);
VALUES(2530, 'He was at school with us. We thought he was our friend!', 94, 11, 20);
VALUES(2531, 'No. Pettigrew''s dead. You killed him!', 94, 1, 20);
VALUES(2532, 'No, he didn''t. I thought so too, until you mentioned seeing Pettigrew on the map!', 94, 11, 20);
VALUES(2533, 'The map was lying, then.', 94, 1, 20);
VALUES(2534, 'The map never lies! Pettigrew''s alive! And he''s right there!', 94, 18, 20);
VALUES(2535, 'Me?! He''s mental!', 94, 2, 20);
VALUES(2536, 'Not you! Your rat!', 94, 18, 20);
VALUES(2537, 'Scabbers has been in my family for...', 94, 2, 20);
VALUES(2538, 'Twelve years? Curiously long life for a common garden rat! He''s missing a toe, isn''t he?', 94, 18, 20);
VALUES(2539, 'So what?', 94, 2, 20);
VALUES(2540, 'All they could find of Pettigrew was his...', 94, 1, 20);
VALUES(2541, 'Finger! That dirty coward cut it off so everyone would think he was dead! And then he transformed into a rat!', 94, 18, 20);
VALUES(2542, 'Show me. Give it to him, Ron.', 94, 1, 20);
VALUES(2543, 'What are you trying to do to him? Scabbers! Leave him alone! Get off him! What are you doing?', 94, 2, 20);
VALUES(2544, 'Remus? Sirius. My old friends! Harry! Look at you! You look so much like your father! Like James! We were the best of friends...', 94, 44, 20);
VALUES(2545, 'How dare you speak to Harry! How dare you talk about James in front of him!', 94, 18, 20);
VALUES(2546, 'You sold James and Lily to Voldemort, didn''t you?', 94, 11, 20);
VALUES(2547, 'I didn''t mean to! The Dark Lord. You have no idea the weapons he possesses! Ask yourself, Sirius! What would you have done? What would you have done?', 94, 44, 20);
VALUES(2548, 'I would have died! I would have died, rather than betray my friends!', 94, 18, 20);
VALUES(2549, 'Harry, James wouldn''t have wanted me killed! Your dad... Your dad would have spared me! He would show me mercy!', 94, 44, 20);
VALUES(2550, 'You should''ve realized, Peter, that if Voldemort didn''t kill you, then we would! Together!', 94, 11, 20);
VALUES(2551, 'No!', 94, 1, 20);
VALUES(2552, 'Harry, this man...', 94, 11, 20);
VALUES(2553, 'I know what he is. But we''ll take him to the castle.', 94, 1, 20);
VALUES(2554, 'Bless you, boy! Bless you!', 94, 44, 20);
VALUES(2555, 'Get off! I said we''d take you to the castle. After that, the dementors can have you.', 94, 1, 20);
VALUES(2556, 'Sorry about the bite. I reckon that twinges a bit.', 95, 18, 67);
VALUES(2557, 'A bit? A bit? You almost tore my leg off!', 95, 2, 67);
VALUES(2558, 'I was going for the rat. Normally, I have a very sweet disposition as a dog. In fact, more than once, James suggested that I make the change permanent. The tail I could live with. But the fleas, they''re murder.', 95, 18, 67);
VALUES(2559, 'Okay.', 95, 1, 67);
VALUES(2560, 'You better go.', 95, 2, 67);
VALUES(2561, 'No. Don''t worry, okay? It''s fine. I''ll stay.', 95, 1, 67);
VALUES(2562, 'You go, I''ll stay.', 95, 3, 67);
VALUES(2563, 'You okay?', 95, 1, 67);
VALUES(2564, 'I''m fine. Go.', 95, 2, 67);
VALUES(2565, 'That looks really painful.', 95, 3, 67);
VALUES(2566, 'So painful. They might chop it.', 95, 2, 67);
VALUES(2567, 'I''m sure Madam Pomfrey will fix it in a heartbeat.', 95, 3, 67);
VALUES(2568, 'It''s too late. It''s ruined. It''ll have to be chopped off.', 95, 2, 67);
VALUES(2569, 'It''s beautiful, isn''t it? I''ll never forget the first time I walked through those doors. It''ll be nice to do it again as a free man. That was a noble thing you did back there. He doesn''t deserve it.', 95, 18, 67);
VALUES(2570, 'Well I just didn''t think my dad would have wanted his two best friends... to become killers. Besides, dead, the truth dies with him. Alive, you''re free.', 95, 1, 67);
VALUES(2571, 'Turn me into a maggot! Turn me into a flobberworm! Anything but the dementors! Ron! Haven''t I been a good friend? A good pet? You won''t let them give me to the dementors, will you? I was your rat! Sweet girl! Clever girl! Surely you won''t let them...', 95, 44, 67);
VALUES(2572, 'Get away from her!', 95, 11, 67);
VALUES(2573, 'I don''t know if you know, Harry... but when you were born, James and Lily made me your godfather.', 95, 18, 67);
VALUES(2574, 'I know.', 95, 1, 67);
VALUES(2575, 'I can understand if you choose to stay with your aunt and uncle... but if you ever wanted a different home...', 95, 18, 67);
VALUES(2576, 'What? Come and live with you?', 95, 1, 67);
VALUES(2577, 'It''s just a thought. I can understand if you don''t want to.', 95, 18, 67);
VALUES(2578, 'Harry!', 95, 3, 67);
VALUES(2579, 'Remus, my old friend! Have you taken your potion tonight? You know the man you truly are, Remus! This heart is where you truly live! This heart here! This flesh is only flesh!', 95, 18, 67);
VALUES(2580, 'Expelliarmus!', 95, 1, 67);
VALUES(2581, 'Harry!', 95, 3, 67);
VALUES(2582, 'Remus! Remus! Run! Run!', 95, 18, 67);
VALUES(2583, 'Come on.', 95, 1, 67);
VALUES(2584, 'Wait! Wait!', 95, 3, 67);
VALUES(2585, 'Hermione! Bad idea. Bad idea.', 95, 2, 67);
VALUES(2586, 'Professor? Professor Lupin?', 95, 3, 67);
VALUES(2587, 'Nice doggy. Nice doggy!', 95, 2, 67);
VALUES(2588, 'There you are, Potter!', 95, 6, 67);
VALUES(2589, 'Sirius!', 95, 1, 67);
VALUES(2590, 'Come back here, Potter!', 95, 6, 67);
VALUES(2591, 'Sirius! No. Sirius! Expecto Patronum!', 96, 1, 37);
VALUES(2592, 'Harry?', 96, 3, 37);
VALUES(2593, 'I saw my dad.', 97, 1, 43);
VALUES(2594, 'What?', 97, 3, 43);
VALUES(2595, 'He sent the dementors away. I saw him across the lake.', 97, 1, 43);
VALUES(2596, 'Listen Harry, they''ve captured Sirius. Any minute the dementors are going to perform the Kiss.', 97, 3, 43);
VALUES(2597, 'You mean they''re gonna kill him?', 97, 1, 43);
VALUES(2598, 'No. It''s worse. Much worse. They''re going to suck out his soul. Headmaster, you''ve got to stop them. They''ve got the wrong man.', 97, 3, 43);
VALUES(2599, 'It''s true. Sirius is innocent.', 97, 1, 43);
VALUES(2600, 'It''s Scabbers who did it.', 97, 2, 43);
VALUES(2601, 'Scabbers?', 97, 4, 43);
VALUES(2602, 'He''s my rat, sir. He''s not really a rat. He was a rat. He was my brother Percy''s rat. But then they gave him an owl...', 97, 2, 43);
VALUES(2603, 'The point is, we know the truth. Please believe us.', 97, 3, 43);
VALUES(2604, 'I do, Miss Granger. But the word of three 13-year-old wizards will convince few others. A child''s voice, however honest and true... is meaningless to those who have forgotten how to listen. Mysterious thing, time. Powerful... and when meddled with, dangerous. Sirius Black is in the topmost cell of the Dark Tower. You know the laws, Miss Granger. You must not be seen. And you would do well, I feel, to return before this last chime. If not, the consequences are too ghastly to discuss. If you succeed tonight... more than one innocent life may be spared. Three turns should do it, I think. Oh, and by the way. When in doubt, I find retracing my steps to be a wise place to begin. Good luck.', 97, 4, 43);
VALUES(2605, 'What the bloody hell was that all about?', 97, 2, 43);
VALUES(2606, 'Sorry, Ron, but seeing as you can''t walk...', 97, 3, 43);
VALUES(2607, 'What just happened? Where''s Ron?', 98, 1, 43);
VALUES(2608, '7:30. Where were we at 7:30?', 98, 3, 43);
VALUES(2609, 'I don''t know. Going to Hagrid''s?', 98, 1, 43);
VALUES(2610, 'Come on. And we can''t be seen.', 98, 3, 43);
VALUES(2611, 'Hermione! Hermione! Hermione, wait. Hermione, will you please tell me what it is we''re doing?', 98, 1, 40);
VALUES(2612, 'You foul, loathsome, evil little cockroach!', 98, 3, 40);
VALUES(2613, 'That''s us.', 98, 1, 40);
VALUES(2614, 'Hermione, no! He''s not worth it.', 98, 2, 40);
VALUES(2615, 'This is not normal.', 98, 1, 40);
VALUES(2616, 'This is a Time-Turner, Harry. McGonagall gave it to me first term. This is how I''ve been getting to my lessons all year.', 98, 3, 40);
VALUES(3099, 'Nothing.', 116, 1, 51);
VALUES(2617, 'You mean we''ve gone back in time?', 98, 1, 40);
VALUES(2618, 'Yes. Dumbledore obviously wanted us to return to this moment. Clearly, something happened he wants us to change.', 98, 3, 40);
VALUES(2619, 'Good punch.', 98, 1, 40);
VALUES(2620, 'Thanks. Malfoy''s coming.', 98, 3, 40);
VALUES(2621, 'Run.', 98, 80, 40);
VALUES(2622, 'Not a word to anyone, understood? I''m gonna get that jumped-up mudblood! Mark my words.', 98, 12, 40);
VALUES(2623, 'That felt good.', 98, 3, 40);
VALUES(2624, 'Not good, brilliant.', 98, 2, 40);
VALUES(2625, 'Come on. We should be at Hagrid''s.', 98, 1, 40);
VALUES(2626, 'Look. Buckbeak''s still alive.', 99, 1, 40);
VALUES(2627, 'Of course. Remember what Dumbledore said? If we succeed, more than one innocent life could be spared. Let''s go.', 99, 3, 40);
VALUES(2628, 'Here they come. I''d better hurry.', 99, 1, 40);
VALUES(2629, 'Fudge has to see Buckbeak before we steal him. Otherwise, he''ll think Hagrid set him free.', 99, 3, 40);
VALUES(2630, 'Scabbers, you''re alive!', 99, 2, 40);
VALUES(2631, 'Keep a closer eye on your pet, Ron.', 99, 5, 40);
VALUES(2632, 'That''s Pettigrew.', 99, 1, 40);
VALUES(2633, 'Harry, you can''t.', 99, 3, 40);
VALUES(2634, 'He betrayed my parents. You don''t expect me to sit here.', 99, 1, 40);
VALUES(2635, 'Yes, and you must! Harry, you''re in Hagrid''s hut now. If you just go bursting in, you''ll think you''ve gone mad. Awful things happen to wizards who meddle with time. We can''t be seen.', 99, 3, 40);
VALUES(2636, 'Fudge is coming. And we aren''t leaving? Why aren''t we leaving?', 99, 3, 40);
VALUES(2637, 'Are you mad?', 99, 1, 40);
VALUES(2638, 'Ow!', 99, 1, 40);
VALUES(2639, 'Ow! That hurt!', 99, 1, 40);
VALUES(2640, 'Sorry. We''re coming out the back door. Go!', 99, 3, 40);
VALUES(2641, 'Is that really what my hair looks like from the back?', 99, 3, 40);
VALUES(2642, 'What?', 99, 1, 40);
VALUES(2643, 'I thought I just saw... Never mind.', 99, 3, 40);
VALUES(2644, 'Let''s go.', 99, 2, 40);
VALUES(2645, 'Okay, go, Harry. Go!', 99, 3, 40);
VALUES(2646, 'Get away. Get off.', 99, 1, 40);
VALUES(2647, 'Minister, I really think I should sign as well.', 99, 4, 40);
VALUES(2648, 'Yes, very well. Perhaps it would be...', 99, 17, 40);
VALUES(2649, 'Okay, Buckbeak. Come quickly. Come with us now. Come on.', 99, 3, 40);
VALUES(2650, 'Keep trying. Come on. Quickly. Buckbeak. Okay? Quickly. Hurry up. Okay?', 99, 3, 40);
VALUES(2651, 'Your name only.', 99, 17, 40);
VALUES(2652, 'It''s such a very long name...', 99, 4, 40);
VALUES(2653, 'Hurry up now, Buckbeak, okay? Come on. Come on, Buckbeak. Come and get the nice dead ferret. Come on. It''s here. Come on, Beaky.', 99, 3, 40);
VALUES(2654, 'Here we are, minister. Follow me. Now, look there.', 99, 4, 40);
VALUES(2655, 'Where?', 99, 17, 40);
