VALUES(2696, 'That''s great.', 100, 3, 67);
VALUES(2697, 'When we free him, I''ll never have to go back to the Dursleys''. It''ll just be me and him. We could live in the country... someplace you can see the sky. I think he''ll like that after all those years in Azkaban.', 100, 1, 67);
VALUES(2698, 'Harry! Run!', 100, 3, 67);
VALUES(2699, 'Let''s go! What are you doing?', 100, 1, 67);
VALUES(2700, 'Saving your life!', 100, 3, 67);
VALUES(2701, 'Thanks. Great! Now he''s coming for us.', 100, 1, 67);
VALUES(2702, 'Yeah, I didn''t think about that. Run!', 100, 3, 67);
VALUES(2703, 'That was so scary.', 100, 3, 67);
VALUES(2704, 'Poor Professor Lupin''s having a really tough night. Sirius! Come on!', 100, 1, 67);
VALUES(2705, 'This is horrible.', 100, 3, 37);
VALUES(2706, 'Don''t worry. My dad will come. He''ll conjure the Patronus. Any minute now! Right there! You''ll see!', 100, 1, 37);
VALUES(2707, 'Harry, listen to me. No one''s coming.', 100, 3, 37);
VALUES(2708, 'Don''t worry, he will! He will come! Sirius.', 100, 1, 37);
VALUES(2709, 'You''re dying... both of you. Harry!', 100, 3, 37);
VALUES(2710, 'Expecto Patronum!', 100, 1, 37);
VALUES(2711, 'You were right, Hermione. It wasn''t my dad I saw earlier. It was me! I saw myself conjuring the Patronus before. I knew I could do it this time because... well, I had already done it. Does that make sense?', 100, 1, 37);
VALUES(2712, 'No.', 100, 3, 37);
VALUES(2713, 'But I don''t like flying...!', 100, 3, 37);
VALUES(2714, 'Bombarda!', 100, 3, 37);
VALUES(2715, 'I''ll be forever grateful for this... to both of you.', 100, 18, 37);
VALUES(2716, 'I want to go with you.', 100, 1, 37);
VALUES(2717, 'One day, perhaps. For some time, my life will be too unpredictable. And besides... you''re meant to be here.', 100, 18, 37);
VALUES(2718, 'But you''re innocent.', 100, 1, 37);
VALUES(2719, 'And you know it. And for now, that will do. I expect you''re tired of hearing this... but you look so like your father. Except your eyes. You have...', 100, 18, 37);
VALUES(2720, 'My mother''s eyes.', 100, 1, 37);
VALUES(2721, 'It''s cruel that I spent so much time with James and Lily, and you so little. But know this: The ones that love us never really leave us. And you can always find them... in here. You really are the brightest witch of your age.', 100, 18, 37);
VALUES(2722, 'We have to go.', 100, 3, 37);
VALUES(2723, 'Well?', 101, 4, 43);
VALUES(2724, 'He''s free. We did it.', 101, 1, 43);
VALUES(2725, 'Did what? Good night.', 101, 4, 43);
VALUES(2726, 'How did you get there? I was talking to you there. And now you''re there.', 101, 2, 43);
VALUES(2727, 'What''s he talking about, Harry?', 101, 3, 43);
VALUES(2728, 'I don''t know. Honestly, Ron. How can somebody be in two places at once?', 102, 1, 43);
VALUES(2729, 'Hello, Harry. I saw you coming. I''ve looked worse, believe me.', 102, 11, 30);
