VALUES(4589, 'I asked you why Voldemort tried to kill me.', 156, 1, 41);
VALUES(4590, 'You have no idea the pain it causes me to tell it to you, even now. But unfortunately, I must.', 156, 4, 41);
VALUES(4591, 'I don''t understand, Professor.', 156, 1, 41);
VALUES(4592, 'Professor, why am I so important to', 156, 1, 41);
VALUES(4593, 'An excellent question, Harry. The answer lies in the prophesy.', 156, 4, 41);
VALUES(4594, 'Sir, it got smashed.', 156, 1, 41);
VALUES(4595, 'That was not the only place the Prophesy is preserved.', 156, 4, 41);
VALUES(4596, '"The One with the power to vanquish the Dark Lord approaches....Born to', 156, 38, 41);
VALUES(4597, 'I''m not sure I understand all that, sir...', 156, 1, 41);
VALUES(4598, 'And...it means me?', 156, 1, 41);
VALUES(4599, 'Interestingly, there were two boys whom the prophesy could have been referring to. You and Neville Longbottom.', 156, 4, 41);
VALUES(4600, 'So it''s not necessarily me, sir?', 156, 1, 41);
VALUES(4601, 'What if he chose wrong?', 156, 1, 41);
VALUES(4602, 'Why didn''t he wait? Why attack when we were babies?', 156, 1, 41);
VALUES(4603, 'Voldemort had an informant listening to my meeting with Professor Trelawney. Fortunately he was discovered before he could hear the entire prophesy. Voldemort had to act immediately, he didn''t know the rest of the prophesy. All he knew was that he had to destroy the child who would grow to be a threat to his power.', 156, 4, 41);
VALUES(4604, 'But I don''t have any special powers.', 156, 1, 41);
VALUES(4605, 'There is a room in the Department of Mysteries which is kept locked at all times. It contains a force so wonderful and yet terrible that it is greater than death itself. It is that power which you have incredible amounts of and of which Voldemort has none.', 156, 4, 41);
VALUES(4606, 'What is it, sir?', 156, 1, 41);
VALUES(4607, 'There is only the end of the prophesy which we haven''t addressed. It states "neither can live while the other survives."', 156, 4, 41);
VALUES(4608, 'It is the final burden which I must place on you, Harry.', 156, 4, 41);
VALUES(4609, 'One of us has to kill the other...in the end.', 156, 1, 41);
