VALUES(5735, 'Severus.  I was beginning to worry you''d lost your way.  Come.  I''ve saved you a seat.', 185, 9, 13);
VALUES(5736, 'You know our hosts, of course, Severus.  Narcissa in particular has been most hospitable.  Lucius, on the other hand, is, I fear, burdened by my presence.  Are you, Lucius?', 185, 9, 13);
VALUES(5737, 'My lord?', 185, 23, 13);
VALUES(5738, 'Are you burdened?', 185, 9, 13);
VALUES(5739, 'My lord is always welcome here.', 185, 63, 13);
VALUES(5740, 'You bring news I trust, Severus?', 185, 9, 13);
VALUES(5741, 'It will happen Saturday next.  At nightfall.', 185, 6, 13);
VALUES(5742, 'And this information comes --', 185, 9, 13);
VALUES(5743, '-- from the source we discussed.', 185, 6, 13);
VALUES(5744, 'I have heard differently, my lord. Dawlish, the Auror, let slip that the Potter boy will not be moved until the thirtieth of this month, the night before he turns seventeen.', 185, 70, 13);
VALUES(5745, 'This is a false trail.  The Auror Office no longer plays any part in the protection of Harry Potter. Those closest to him believe we have infiltrated the Ministry.', 185, 6, 13);
VALUES(5746, 'Well, they''ve got that right, then, ''aven''t they?', 185, 129, 13);
VALUES(5747, 'Pius, what say you?', 185, 9, 13);
VALUES(5748, 'One hears many things, my lord. Whether the truth is among them is not clear.', 185, 96, 13);
VALUES(5749, 'Spoken like a true politician. You will, I think, prove most useful, Pius.  Where will he be taken?  The boy?', 185, 9, 13);
VALUES(5750, 'To a safehouse.  Likely the home of someone in the Order.  I''m told it has been given every manner of protection possible. Once there, it will be impractical to attack him.  We may have compromised the Ministry, but there are those who remain loyal to him.  As long as the Ministry stands, his allies within will have the means at their disposal to insure his safety.', 185, 6, 13);
VALUES(5751, 'My lord, if I might, I''d like to volunteer myself for this task. I''d like to kill the boy.', 185, 22, 13);
VALUES(5752, 'Wormtail!  Have I not spoken to you about keeping our guest quiet?', 185, 9, 13);
VALUES(5753, 'Yes, m-my lord.  Right away, my lord.', 185, 44, 13);
VALUES(5754, 'As inspiring as I find your bloodlust, Bellatrix, I must be the one to kill Harry Potter.  But I face an unfortunate complication.  It has recently come to my attention that my wand and Potter''s share the same core. They are, in some ways, twins.  We can wound but not fatally harm one another.  Which means, if I am to kill him... I will have to do it with another''s wand.', 185, 9, 13);
VALUES(5755, 'Come now.  Surely one of you would like the honor?  What about... you, Lucius?', 185, 9, 13);
VALUES(5756, 'I require your wand.', 185, 9, 13);
VALUES(5757, 'Do I detect elm?', 185, 9, 13);
VALUES(5758, 'Yes, my lord.', 185, 23, 13);
VALUES(5759, 'And the core?', 185, 9, 13);
VALUES(5760, 'Dragon -- dragon heartstring.', 185, 23, 13);
VALUES(5761, 'My wand?  You can''t possibly think I would give you my wand.', 185, 9, 13);
VALUES(5762, 'No, my lord.', 185, 23, 13);
VALUES(5763, 'For those of you who do not know, we are joined tonight by Miss Charity Burbage who until recently taught at Hogwarts School of Witchcraft and Wizardry.  Her specialty was Muggle studies. It is Miss Burbage''s belief that Muggles are not so different from us.', 185, 9, 13);
VALUES(5764, 'She would, given her way, have us mate with them.  To her, the mixture of magical and Muggle blood is not an abomination but something to be encouraged.  I, of course, take a contrary view.  But we''re all civilized here.  All adults.  We can agree to disagree.', 185, 9, 13);
VALUES(5765, 'Severus, please.  We''re friends...', 185, 121, 13);
VALUES(5766, 'Avada Kedavra!', 185, 9, 13);
VALUES(5767, 'Nagini... Dinner.', 185, 9, 13);
VALUES(5768, 'Come now, Dudley.  Hurry up!', 186, 21, 8);
