VALUES(5933, 'This.  Despite the fact that neither of your friends appear to have been particularly close to their recently deceased Headmaster, he saw fit to remember them in his will.  Now why do you suppose that would be?', 189, 51, 17);
VALUES(5934, 'No idea.', 189, 1, 17);
VALUES(5935, 'Come now, you don''t expect me to believe...', 189, 51, 17);
VALUES(5936, '''Herein is set forth the Last Will and Testament of Albus Percival Wulfric Brian Dumbledore.  First, to Ronald Bilius Weasley, I leave my Deluminator, a device of my own making, in the hope that -- when things seem most dark -- it will show him the light.''', 189, 51, 17);
VALUES(5937, 'Dumbledore left this?  For me? Brilliant.  Er -- what is it?', 189, 2, 17);
VALUES(5938, 'Wicked.', 189, 2, 17);
VALUES(5939, '''To Miss Hermione Jean Granger, I leave my copy of The Tales of Beedle the Bard, in the hope that she will find it entertaining and instructive.''', 189, 51, 17);
VALUES(5940, 'Mum used to read me those!  The Wizard and the Hopping Pot, Babbitty Rabbity and her Cackling Stump...', 189, 2, 17);
VALUES(5941, 'Oh, c''mon!  Beedle''s stories are famous!  Babbity Rabbitty? No...?', 189, 2, 17);
VALUES(5942, '''To Harry James Potter, I leave the Snitch he caught in his first Quidditch match at Hogwarts, as a reminder of the rewards of perseverance and skill.', 189, 51, 17);
VALUES(5943, 'That''s it then?', 189, 1, 17);
VALUES(5944, 'Not quite.  Dumbledore left you a second bequest:  The Sword of Godric Gryffindor.  Unfortunately, the Sword of Gryffindor was not Dumbledore''s to give away.  As an important historical artifact, it belongs...', 189, 51, 17);
VALUES(5945, 'To Harry!  It belongs to Harry! It chose him!  It came to him in the Chamber of Secrets when he most needed it!', 189, 3, 17);
VALUES(5946, 'The sword may present itself to any worthy Gryffindor, Miss Granger.  That does not make it that wizard''s property.  And in any event the current whereabouts of the sword are unknown.', 189, 51, 17);
VALUES(5947, 'Excuse me?', 189, 1, 17);
VALUES(5948, 'The sword is missing. I won''t pretend to be your friend, Mr. Potter.  But I assure you I''m not your enemy.', 189, 51, 17);
VALUES(5949, 'You''ll forgive me, Minister.  But it''s a little hard to tell the difference these days.', 189, 1, 17);
