VALUES(5965, 'Mr. Potter!  By all means!', 190, 62, 17);
VALUES(5966, 'I found what you wrote in the Daily Prophet very moving, sir.  I take it you knew Professor Dumbledore well?', 190, 1, 17);
VALUES(5967, 'I certainly knew him the longest, if you don''t count his brother Aberforth -- and somehow, people never do seem to count Aberforth.', 190, 62, 17);
VALUES(5968, 'I never even knew he had a brother, sir.', 190, 1, 17);
VALUES(5969, 'Yes, well, Dumbledore was always very private.  Even as a boy.', 190, 62, 17);
VALUES(5970, 'Sir, I was wondering if you''d had much contact with him before he died.', 190, 1, 17);
VALUES(5971, 'The occasional owl.  Though it was strange...', 190, 62, 17);
VALUES(5972, 'Strange, sir?', 190, 1, 17);
VALUES(5973, 'It was the owls themselves.  They often arrived in distress.  It was clear they''d traveled great distances in some cases.', 190, 62, 17);
VALUES(5974, 'Could you tell me from where they''d come, sir?', 190, 1, 17);
VALUES(5975, 'I''m afraid not.  Albus'' messages mostly referenced our days together as schoolboys.  They were surprisingly intimate.  When he did speak of his current activities his words would turn elliptical.  Still, I sensed he was under great stress.  Why do you ask?', 190, 62, 17);
VALUES(5976, 'Just curious.  I was... close to Professor Dumbledore.', 190, 1, 17);
VALUES(5977, 'Well, he treasured you, Mr. Potter, I can attest to that.  I can also tell you that when a person passes, it''s only natural to rue the things left unsaid, to regret the question never asked. I knew Albus nigh on 100 years, but in many ways he will always remain a riddle even to me.', 190, 62, 17);
VALUES(5978, 'Don''t despair, Elphias.  I''m told he''s been thoroughly unriddled by Rita Skeeter.  In 800 pages no less.', 190, 140, 17);
VALUES(5979, 'That woman is a vulture, Muriel, and you well know it.', 190, 62, 17);
VALUES(5980, 'Someone has to pick the bones to get at the truth.  I read your obituary, Elphias.  Lovely.  But you did skate over some of the sticky patches in Dumbledore''s life.', 190, 77, 17);
VALUES(5981, 'I''m sorry you think so, Muriel.  I assure you I was writing from the heart.', 190, 62, 17);
VALUES(5982, 'Yes, well, Rita Skeeter hasn''t made that mistake, I''m sure.  Word has it someone talked to her, someone who knew the Dumbledore family well.  You and I both know who that is, Elphias.', 190, 77, 17);
VALUES(5983, 'A monstrous betrayal.  I can only conclude the rumors are true and that she has become untethered.', 190, 62, 17);
VALUES(5984, 'Who are you talking about?', 190, 1, 17);
VALUES(5985, 'Well, I don''t suppose it''ll be a secret once the book comes out. Bathilda Bagshot.', 190, 77, 17);
VALUES(5986, 'Who?', 190, 1, 17);
VALUES(5987, 'Who? Bathilda Bagshot!  My god, boy, she''s only the most celebrated magical historian of the last century.  Don''t they read History of Magic at Hogwarts anymore?', 190, 77, 17);
VALUES(5988, 'Oh, right.  Slipped my mind...', 190, 1, 17);
VALUES(5989, 'She knew the Dumbledores as well as anyone.  She''d have letters, perhaps an interesting photograph or two.  I''m sure Rita Skeeter would have thought it well worth a trip to Godric''s Hollow to take a peek into that old bird''s rattled cage.', 190, 77, 17);
VALUES(5990, 'Godric''s Hollow?  Bathilda Bagshot lives in Godric''s Hollow?', 190, 1, 17);
VALUES(5991, 'For years now.  That''s where she first met Dumbledore.', 190, 77, 17);
VALUES(5992, 'Excuse me?  You don''t mean to say Dumbledore lived there too?', 190, 1, 17);
VALUES(5993, 'Of course.  The family moved there after his father killed those three Muggles.  It was quite the scandal. Honestly, my boy, are you sure you knew him at all?', 190, 77, 17);
VALUES(5994, 'The Ministry has fallen.  The Minister of Magic is dead.  They are coming...', 190, 56, 17);
VALUES(5995, 'Nice meeting you, Mr. Potter!', 190, 62, 17);
VALUES(5996, 'Ron!  Ron!', 190, 3, 17);
VALUES(5997, 'Harry!  Go!  Go!', 190, 11, 17);
VALUES(5998, 'Where are we?', 191, 2, 7);
VALUES(5999, 'Shaftesbury Avenue.  I used to come here to the theater with my mum and dad.  Just popped into my head.  I don''t know why...', 191, 3, 7);
VALUES(6000, 'This way!', 191, 3, 7);
VALUES(6001, 'We need to change.', 191, 3, 7);
VALUES(6002, 'How the ruddy --', 191, 2, 7);
VALUES(6003, 'Undetectable Extension Charm.', 191, 3, 7);
VALUES(6004, 'You''re amazing, you are.', 191, 2, 7);
VALUES(6005, 'Always the tone of surprise.', 191, 3, 7);
VALUES(6006, 'That''ll be the books.', 191, 3, 7);
VALUES(6007, 'Do you reckon everyone''s alright at the wedding?  Maybe we should --', 191, 1, 7);
VALUES(6008, 'They were after you, mate.  We''d just put everyone in danger going back.', 191, 2, 7);
VALUES(6009, 'Ron''s right.  Cappuccino, please.', 191, 3, 7);
VALUES(6010, 'What she said.', 191, 2, 7);
VALUES(6011, 'Same.', 191, 1, 7);
VALUES(6012, 'Wicked scar.', 191, 140, 7);
VALUES(6013, 'So where do we go from here?  The Leaky Cauldron?', 191, 2, 7);
VALUES(6014, 'Too dangerous.  If Voldemort''s taken over the Ministry, none of the old places are safe.', 191, 3, 7);
VALUES(6015, 'My rucksack.  With all my things. I left it back at the Burrow --', 191, 1, 7);
VALUES(6016, 'You''re joking.', 191, 1, 7);
VALUES(6017, 'I''ve had the essentials packed for days.  Just in case.', 191, 3, 7);
VALUES(6018, 'By the way -- these jeans?  Not my favorite.  Bit tight.', 191, 2, 7);
VALUES(6019, 'Down!', 191, 1, 7);
VALUES(6020, 'Stupefy!', 191, 1, 7);
VALUES(6021, 'Petrificus Totalus! Go.', 191, 3, 7);
VALUES(6022, 'She doesn''t argue.', 191, 3, 7);
VALUES(6023, 'Lock the door, get the lights.', 191, 1, 7);
VALUES(6024, 'This one''s name is Rowle.  He was on the Astronomy Tower the night Snape killed Dumbledore.', 191, 1, 7);
VALUES(6025, 'This is Dolohov.  I recognize him from the wanted posters.', 191, 2, 7);
VALUES(6026, 'So what do we do with you, huh? Kill us if it was turned round, wouldn''t you?', 191, 2, 7);
VALUES(6027, 'Suppose it''s him that did Mad-Eye. How would you feel then?', 191, 2, 7);
VALUES(6028, 'It''s better we wipe their memories.  We kill them, they''ll know we were here.', 191, 1, 7);
VALUES(6029, 'You''re the boss. Hermione?', 191, 2, 7);
VALUES(6030, 'You''re the best with spells.', 191, 2, 7);
VALUES(6031, 'Obliviate.', 191, 3, 7);
VALUES(6032, 'How is it they knew we were there?', 191, 1, 7);
VALUES(6033, 'Maybe you still have the Trace on you.', 191, 3, 7);
VALUES(6034, 'Can''t be. The Trace breaks at seventeen. It''s Wizarding law.', 191, 2, 7);
VALUES(6035, 'What?', 191, 2, 7);
VALUES(6036, 'We didn''t celebrate your birthday, Harry.  Ginny and I -- we''d prepared a cake.  We were going to bring it out at the end of the wedding...', 191, 3, 7);
VALUES(6037, 'Hermione.  I appreciate the thought -- honestly.  But given that we were almost killed by a couple of Death Eaters a few minutes ago...', 191, 1, 7);
VALUES(6038, 'Right.  Perspective.', 191, 3, 7);
VALUES(6039, 'We''ve got to get off the streets, get somewhere safe.', 191, 2, 7);
VALUES(6040, 'I have an idea.', 191, 1, 7);
VALUES(6041, 'Severus Snape?', 191, 13, 7);
VALUES(6042, 'Mad-Eye...?', 191, 1, 7);
VALUES(6043, 'What was that about?', 191, 2, 7);
VALUES(6044, 'Mad-eye''s doing, I''d guess.  In case Snape decided to come snooping.', 191, 3, 7);
VALUES(6045, 'Homenum revelio.', 191, 3, 7);
VALUES(6046, 'It''s a spell to reveal human presence.', 191, 3, 7);
VALUES(6047, 'We''re alone.', 191, 3, 7);
VALUES(6048, 'Lumos.', 191, 1, 7);
VALUES(6049, 'Dear Sirius.  Thank you for Harry''s birthday present.  You''d think he''d been born on a broom.', 191, 45, 7);
VALUES(6050, 'James says he''s got the look of a Seeker, but then James would.  We had a very quiet birthday tea, just us and old Bathilda, who dotes on Harry.  Wormy dropped by late in the day, but seemed down and didn''t stay long.  James is frustrated being shut up here, but Dumbledore''s still got his Invisibility Cloak, so he doesn''t have much choice.  By the way, Bathilda tells the most amazing stories about our old Headmaster. I don''t know how much to believe. Can it really be true that Dumbledore --', 191, 45, 7);
VALUES(6051, 'Harry!  Harry!', 191, 3, 7);
VALUES(6052, 'Ron!  I''ve found him!', 191, 3, 7);
VALUES(6053, 'Good!  Tell him from me he''s a git!', 191, 2, 7);
VALUES(6054, 'Harry, you can''t just disappear. We thought --', 191, 3, 7);
VALUES(6055, 'It''s from your Mum.  To Sirius. Bathilda Bagshot...?', 191, 3, 7);
VALUES(6056, 'Yeah.  They knew her.  She wrote A History of Magic, you know.', 191, 1, 7);
VALUES(6057, 'Did she now?', 191, 3, 7);
VALUES(6058, 'I''m thinking maybe we should go talk to her.  She still lives in Godric''s Hollow.  I''m thinking maybe she could help us.', 191, 1, 7);
VALUES(6059, 'Harry.  I can imagine why you''d want to go there, but... I don''t think Bathilda Bagshot is going to know where Voldemort hid his Horcruxes.', 191, 3, 7);
VALUES(6060, 'Hey!  I think you two better come down here.', 191, 2, 7);
VALUES(6061, 'The two clinging to the tree are Death Eaters for sure.  Dunno ''bout the bloke on the bench. Can''t see us, of course.  But we''ll have to be careful coming and going.  C''mon.  There''s something else you need to see.', 191, 2, 7);
VALUES(6062, 'Lovely.', 191, 3, 7);
VALUES(6063, 'To the Dark Lord.  I know I will be dead long before you read this... I have stolen the real Horcrux and intend to destroy it...', 191, 1, 7);
VALUES(6064, 'R.A.B. was Sirius'' brother?', 191, 2, 7);
VALUES(6065, 'Yes.  Question is, did he actually destroy the real Horcrux?', 191, 3, 7);
VALUES(6066, 'Stop!  I order you!', 192, 1, 7);
VALUES(6067, 'Kreacher...', 192, 2, 7);
VALUES(6068, 'Been spying on us, have you?', 192, 1, 7);
VALUES(6069, 'Kreacher has been... watching. Kreacher always watches.', 192, 48, 7);
VALUES(6070, 'Maybe he knows.', 192, 3, 7);
VALUES(6071, 'Ever seen this before?', 192, 1, 7);
VALUES(6072, 'Kreacher, I own this place. Sirius left it to me.  Which means I own you too.', 192, 1, 7);
VALUES(6073, 'That was Master Regulus'' locket.', 192, 48, 7);
VALUES(6074, 'That''s right.  But there were two, weren''t there?', 192, 1, 7);
VALUES(6075, 'Where''s the other one?', 192, 1, 7);
VALUES(6076, 'Kreacher doesn''t know where the other locket is.', 192, 48, 7);
VALUES(6077, 'But was it here?  Did you ever see it?', 192, 3, 7);
VALUES(6078, 'Filthy Mudblood -- The Death Eaters will soon be coming for you!', 192, 48, 7);
VALUES(6079, 'Blood-traitor Weasley --', 192, 48, 7);
VALUES(6080, 'Ron!  RON!', 192, 3, 7);
VALUES(6081, 'Answer her.', 192, 1, 7);
VALUES(6082, 'Yes.  It was here, in this house. A most evil object...', 192, 48, 7);
VALUES(6083, 'How do you mean?', 192, 1, 7);
VALUES(6084, 'Before he died, Master Regulus ordered Kreacher to destroy it. It was the last thing he asked of Kreacher.  But no matter how Kreacher tried, he could not..', 192, 48, 7);
VALUES(6085, 'Where is it now?  Did someone take it, Kreacher?', 192, 1, 7);
VALUES(6086, 'He came in the night.  He took many things, including the locket.', 192, 48, 7);
VALUES(6087, 'Who, Kreacher?  Who was it?', 192, 1, 7);
VALUES(6088, 'Mundungus.  Mundungus Fletcher.', 192, 48, 7);
VALUES(6089, 'Find him.', 192, 1, 7);
VALUES(6090, 'As your new Minister for Magic, I promise to restore this temple of tolerance to its former glory. Therefore, beginning today, each employee will be required to submit themselves for evaluation. But know this:  You have nothing to fear... as long as you have nothing to hide...', 192, 96, 7);
VALUES(6091, 'My father will hear about this.', 192, 71, 7);
VALUES(6092, 'He''s not here, you fools.', 192, 10, 7);
VALUES(6093, 'They have flesh memories.', 192, 3, 7);
VALUES(6094, 'Snitches.  They''re never touched by bare skin until the Seeker captures it.  Even the wizard who fabricates it wears gloves.  That way, if there''s a dispute, the Snitch can identify who first touched it.', 192, 3, 7);
VALUES(6095, 'You mean... it remembers me?', 192, 1, 7);
VALUES(6096, 'When Scrimgeour first gave it to you, I thought it might open at your touch -- that Dumbledore had hidden something in it.', 192, 3, 7);
VALUES(6097, 'Harry Potter!  So long it''s been --', 193, 27, 7);
VALUES(6098, 'Expelliarmus!', 193, 3, 7);
VALUES(6099, 'As requested, Kreacher has returned with the thief Mundungus Fletcher!', 193, 48, 7);
VALUES(6100, 'Dobby has also returned with the thief Mundungus Fletcher!', 193, 27, 7);
VALUES(6101, 'What are you playing at -- setting a pair of bleedin'' ''ouse-elves on me!', 193, 76, 7);
VALUES(6102, 'Dobby was only trying to help! Dobby saw Kreacher in Diagon Alley, which Dobby thought was curious.  And then Dobby heard Kreacher mention Harry Potter''s name, which Dobby thought was very curious.  And then Dobby saw that Kreacher was talking to the thief Mundungus Fletcher, which Dobby thought was very, very --', 193, 27, 7);
VALUES(6673, 'Not long.', 205, 3, 68);
VALUES(6103, 'I''m no thief, you foul little git. I''m a purveyer of rare and wondrous objects --', 193, 76, 7);
VALUES(6104, 'You''re a thief, Dung.  Everyone knows it.', 193, 2, 7);
VALUES(6105, 'Master Weasley!  So good to see you again!', 193, 27, 7);
VALUES(6106, 'Wicked trainers.', 193, 2, 7);
VALUES(6107, 'Listen, I panicked that night, all right?  I never volunteered to die for you, mate.  Can I help it if Mad-Eye fell off his broom --', 193, 76, 7);
VALUES(6108, 'Stop lying!', 193, 3, 7);
VALUES(6109, 'Piece of advice.  Let''s not rehash old times.  Got it... mate?', 193, 2, 7);
VALUES(6110, 'When you turned this place over -- don''t deny it! -- you found a locket, am I right?', 193, 1, 7);
VALUES(6111, 'Why?  Was it valuable?', 193, 76, 7);
VALUES(6112, 'You''ve still got it.', 193, 3, 7);
VALUES(6113, 'No.  He''s worried he should have got more money for it.', 193, 2, 7);
VALUES(6114, 'Wouldn''t be difficult, would it? Bleedin'' gave it away, din'' I? There I was, pitching me wares in Diagon Alley when some ministry hag comes up and asks to see my license.  Says she''s of a mind to lock me up and would''ve, too, she hadn'' taken a fancy to that locket.', 193, 76, 7);
VALUES(6115, 'Who was she?  This witch?', 193, 1, 7);
VALUES(6116, 'Well, she''s right there, in''t she? Bleedin'' bow an'' all.', 193, 76, 7);
VALUES(6117, 'Right. So let''s do it.  Who gets who?', 194, 2, 70);
VALUES(6118, 'Well, unless one of you fancies wearing a skirt...', 194, 3, 70);
VALUES(6119, 'Remember what we said.  Keep your eyes down.  Don''t speak to anyone unless absolutely necessary.  Act as normal as possible.  Just do what you see everyone else doing. We do that -- and with a bit of luck -- we get ourselves inside. And then...', 194, 3, 70);
VALUES(6120, 'It gets really tricky.', 194, 1, 70);
VALUES(6121, 'Correct.', 194, 3, 70);
VALUES(6122, 'This is completely mental.', 194, 1, 70);
VALUES(6123, 'Completely, utterly, without question.', 194, 3, 70);
VALUES(6124, 'The world''s mental.  Come on, drink up.  We''ve got a Horcrux to find.', 194, 2, 70);
VALUES(6125, 'In case you''re interested, I''m Reg Cattermole, Magical Maintenance Department.', 194, 2, 70);
VALUES(6126, 'Mafalda Hopkirk, assistant in the Improper Use of Magic Office.', 194, 3, 70);
VALUES(6127, 'I''m nobody.', 194, 1, 70);
VALUES(6128, 'You''re somebody.  Be careful.', 194, 3, 70);
VALUES(6129, 'Morning, Reg!  Good luck today.', 194, 135, 70);
VALUES(6130, 'Oh... yeah.  Thanks.', 194, 2, 70);
VALUES(6131, 'What do you reckon he meant by ''Good luck.''?', 194, 2, 70);
VALUES(6132, 'Apparently so.', 194, 1, 70);
VALUES(6133, 'That''s bloody disgusting.', 194, 2, 70);
VALUES(6134, 'Are those...?', 194, 1, 70);
VALUES(6135, 'Muggles.  In their rightful place.', 194, 3, 70);
VALUES(6136, 'Move it, will you -- oh, Runcorn! Forgive me...', 194, 135, 70);
VALUES(6137, 'You appear to be quite popular.', 194, 3, 70);
VALUES(6138, 'I gotta tell you, I''m starting to freak out a bit.', 194, 2, 70);
VALUES(6139, 'The Ministry must be hiring young these days.', 194, 1, 70);
VALUES(6140, 'They''re not Ministry.  They''re Snatchers.  They hunt Muggle-borns and blood-traitors for a price.', 194, 2, 70);
VALUES(6141, 'How long did you say this batch of Polyjuice Potion would last, Hermione?', 194, 1, 70);
VALUES(6142, 'I didn''t.', 194, 3, 70);
VALUES(6143, 'Cattlemole!', 194, 70, 70);
VALUES(6144, 'It''s still raining in my office. Two days now.', 194, 70, 70);
VALUES(6145, 'Really?  Have you tried an umbrella?', 194, 2, 70);
VALUES(6146, 'You do realize I''m on my way downstairs, don''t you, Cattermole?', 194, 70, 70);
VALUES(6147, 'Downstairs...?', 194, 2, 70);
VALUES(6148, 'To interrogate your wife!  If my wife''s blood status were in doubt and the Head of the Department of Magical Law Enforcement needed a job doing, I think I''d make it a priority.  You''ve got one hour.', 194, 70, 70);
VALUES(6149, 'Oh my god.  What am I going to do? My wife''s all alone downstairs?', 194, 2, 70);
VALUES(6150, 'Ron.  You don''t have a wife.', 194, 1, 70);
VALUES(6151, 'Look, we''ll go with you --', 194, 1, 70);
VALUES(6152, 'No, that''s mad.  You two find Umbridge.  I''ll be fine.  But how do I stop it raining?', 194, 2, 70);
VALUES(6153, 'Try Finite Incantatem.  Of course if something''s gone wrong with an Atmospheric Charm --', 194, 3, 70);
VALUES(6154, 'Level Two.  Department of Magical Law Enforcement, including Wizengamot Administration Services, Auror Headquarters and Improper Use of Magic Department.', 194, 140, 70);
VALUES(6155, 'This is you.', 194, 3, 70);
VALUES(6156, 'Finite Incantatem, okay.  And if that doesn''t work...?', 194, 2, 70);
VALUES(6157, 'I don''t like him being on his own down there.', 194, 3, 70);
VALUES(6158, 'Ron''s been coming here since he was two years old.  It''s us you should be worrying about.', 194, 1, 70);
VALUES(6159, 'You really have horrible teeth, you know that.', 194, 3, 70);
VALUES(6160, 'I say if we don''t locate Umbridge within the hour, we go find Ron and come back another day.  Deal?', 194, 1, 70);
VALUES(6161, 'Ah, Mafalda!  Travers sent you, did he?  Good.  We''ll go straight down.', 194, 15, 70);
VALUES(6162, 'Oh, yes... of course.', 194, 37, 70);
VALUES(6163, 'Reckon the old hag will be interrogating Mudbloods all day?', 194, 132, 70);
VALUES(6164, 'Sh...careful.', 194, 96, 70);
VALUES(6165, 'Runcorn.', 194, 15, 70);
VALUES(6166, 'Accio locket.', 194, 1, 70);
VALUES(6167, 'All right, all right.  Let''s calm down, shall we?', 194, 135, 70);
VALUES(6168, 'It probably just snuck up here from Experimental Charms.  I think none of us will soon forget last month''s Poisonous Duck...', 194, 135, 70);
VALUES(6169, 'R-Runcorn.', 194, 135, 70);
VALUES(6170, 'M-morning.', 194, 2, 70);
VALUES(6171, 'Ron, it''s me.', 194, 1, 70);
VALUES(6172, 'Harry!  Blimey, I forgot what you looked like.  Where''s Hermione?', 194, 2, 70);
VALUES(6173, 'She went down to the courtrooms with Umbridge --', 194, 1, 70);
VALUES(6174, 'I understand, Wakinda, but I can''t be a party to that.', 194, 16, 70);
VALUES(6175, 'Hello, Reg.  Isn''t Mary in for questioning today?  Try to have faith.  If there''s anything Molly and I can do for you --', 194, 16, 70);
VALUES(6176, 'Let me guess.  It''s raining in Yaxley''s office again?', 194, 140, 70);
VALUES(6177, 'Tell him to try an umbrella.', 194, 16, 70);
VALUES(6178, 'Arthur!  You know you''re being tracked, don''t you?', 194, 1, 70);
VALUES(6179, 'Is that a threat, Runcorn?', 194, 16, 70);
VALUES(6180, 'No, Arthur.  It''s a fact.  They''re watching you.', 194, 1, 70);
VALUES(6181, 'I''ll tell you later.  Let''s find Hermione.', 194, 1, 70);
VALUES(6182, 'Bloody cold down here.', 194, 2, 70);
VALUES(6183, 'I''m half-blood, I tell you!  My father was a wizard!  Look him up! William Alderton!  He worked here for thirty years...', 194, 139, 70);
VALUES(6184, 'What is it?', 194, 2, 70);
VALUES(6185, 'It''s here...', 194, 1, 70);
VALUES(6186, 'Reg...', 194, 83, 70);
VALUES(6187, 'Mary Elizabeth Cattermole?', 194, 15, 70);
VALUES(6188, 'Yes.', 194, 83, 70);
VALUES(6189, 'Mother to Maisie, Ellie and Alfred?  Wife to Reginald?', 194, 15, 70);
VALUES(6190, 'Yes.', 194, 83, 70);
VALUES(6191, 'A wand was taken from you upon your arrival at the Ministry today, Mrs. Cattermole.  Is this that wand?', 194, 15, 70);
VALUES(6192, 'Would you please tell the court from which witch or wizard you took this wand.', 194, 15, 70);
VALUES(6193, 'But I didn''t take it.  I got it in Diagon Alley, at Ollivander''s, when I was eleven.  It chose me.', 194, 83, 70);
VALUES(6194, 'No, no, I don''t think so, Mrs. Cattermole.  Wands only choose witches.  And you are not a witch.', 194, 15, 70);
VALUES(6195, 'But I am!  Tell them, Reg!  Tell them what I am!', 194, 83, 70);
VALUES(6196, 'What the devil are you doing, Albert?', 194, 15, 70);
VALUES(6197, 'You''re lying.  And one mustn''t tell lies, Dolores... Stupefy!', 194, 1, 70);
VALUES(6198, 'Expecto PATRONUM!', 194, 1, 70);
VALUES(6199, 'Relashio!', 194, 3, 70);
VALUES(6200, 'You?  It''s you! Reg, it''s Harry Potter!', 194, 83, 70);
VALUES(6201, '''Tis, isn''t it?  This''ll be one to tell the kids.', 194, 2, 70);
VALUES(6202, 'Harry Potter...?', 194, 135, 70);
VALUES(6203, 'Harry... they''ve seen you.  We''ve got to get out of here.', 194, 3, 70);
VALUES(6204, 'Mary.  Go home.  Get the kids. I''ll... I''ll meet you there.  We have to get out the country, understand?', 194, 2, 70);
VALUES(6205, 'Mary!  Do as I say!', 194, 2, 70);
VALUES(6206, 'I''m sorry.  It''s just --', 194, 2, 70);
VALUES(6207, 'Long story.  Nice meeting you.', 194, 2, 70);
VALUES(6208, 'Piss off.', 194, 2, 70);
VALUES(6209, 'Seal the exits!  Now!', 194, 70, 70);
VALUES(6210, 'Harry, quickly, in my bag, there''s a small bottle labeled ''Essence of Dittany.''', 195, 3, 74);
VALUES(6211, 'Quickly!', 195, 3, 74);
VALUES(6212, 'Accio Dittany.', 195, 1, 74);
VALUES(6213, 'Unstopper it.', 195, 3, 74);
VALUES(6214, 'Hermione.  His arm --', 195, 1, 74);
VALUES(6215, 'Just do it!', 195, 3, 74);
VALUES(6216, 'What happened?  I thought we were going back to Grimmauld Place.', 195, 1, 74);
VALUES(6217, 'We were.  We were there.  But Yaxley had hold of me.  I knew we couldn''t stay once he''d seen, so when he let go I brought us here. Ron got Splinched.  I''m... sorry.', 195, 3, 74);
VALUES(6218, 'Don''t be stupid.', 195, 1, 74);
VALUES(6219, 'It''s all I feel safe doing.', 195, 3, 74);
VALUES(6220, 'Salvio Hexia... Protego Totalum...', 195, 3, 74);
VALUES(6221, 'What''re you doing?', 195, 1, 74);
VALUES(6222, 'Protective enchantments.  I don''t fancy another visit like we had on Shaftesbury Avenue, do you? Especially with Ron like this. You can get going on the tent...', 195, 3, 74);
VALUES(6223, 'Tent?  Where am I supposed to find --', 195, 1, 74);
VALUES(6224, 'Repello Muggletum... Muffliato...', 195, 3, 74);
VALUES(6225, 'How''re the mushrooms?  Seem to be the only edible things growing round here.', 195, 3, 74);
VALUES(6226, 'They''re great.', 195, 1, 74);
VALUES(6227, 'Make sure to leave some for Ron.', 195, 3, 74);
VALUES(6228, 'No problem.', 195, 1, 74);
VALUES(6229, 'How bad is he?', 195, 1, 74);
VALUES(6230, 'He''ll be alright in a few days. Hopefully.  If we could take him to Hogwarts, to Madam Pomfrey --', 195, 3, 74);
VALUES(6231, 'So where do we go next?', 195, 3, 74);
VALUES(6232, 'Dumbledore had a theory.  He felt that the Horcruxes would not be made out of random objects.  And he felt they wouldn''t be hidden randomly either.  We know of three so far.  The ring, which according to Dumbledore belonged to Tom Riddle''s grandfather.  The diary, which belonged to Tom himself. And this, which -- again, according to Dumbledore -- belonged to his mother.', 195, 1, 74);
VALUES(6233, 'It scares me a bit, that, thinking it''s a piece of Vol--', 195, 3, 74);
VALUES(6234, 'No, don''t!  Don''t say it!', 195, 2, 74);
VALUES(6235, 'It''s taboo -- You-Know-Who''s name. That''s how they track people now. It''s how they found us in the cafe that night.', 195, 2, 74);
VALUES(6236, 'How d''you know?', 195, 1, 74);
VALUES(6237, 'I overheard a bloke from the Enforcement office talking about it at the Ministry.  Blimey, what''s that smell?', 195, 2, 74);
VALUES(6238, 'Dinner?', 195, 3, 74);
VALUES(6239, 'Not bloody likely.  Smells like something Ginny would cook.', 195, 2, 74);
VALUES(6240, 'Tea?', 195, 3, 74);
VALUES(6241, 'Is that it?', 195, 2, 74);
VALUES(6242, 'I know.  I felt it too. It''s... it''s like it''s ticking or something, like it has a tiny metal heart, like it''s --', 195, 1, 74);
VALUES(6243, '... alive.', 195, 2, 74);
VALUES(6244, 'I hate it.  It''s like he''s here with us.', 195, 3, 74);
VALUES(6245, 'That''s why we''re going to kill it.', 195, 1, 74);
VALUES(6246, 'Dissendium!', 195, 1, 74);
VALUES(6247, 'Incendio!', 195, 3, 74);
VALUES(6248, 'Expulso!', 195, 1, 74);
VALUES(6249, 'Confringo!', 195, 3, 74);
VALUES(6250, 'It''s angry.', 195, 2, 74);
VALUES(6251, 'What''re you doing?', 195, 3, 74);
VALUES(6252, 'We have to keep it safe until we can figure out how to destroy it.', 195, 1, 74);
VALUES(6253, 'I can put it in my bag --', 195, 3, 74);
VALUES(6254, 'No.', 195, 1, 74);
VALUES(6255, 'Seems strange, mate.  Dumbledore sends you off to find a load of Horcruxes, but doesn''t bother to tell you how to destroy them. Doesn''t that bother you?', 195, 2, 74);
VALUES(6256, 'You wouldn''t be lying to me, would you, Gregorovitch?  Because, I must tell you... that will only make it worse for you...', 195, 9, 74);
VALUES(6257, 'Who was he?  The thief?', 195, 9, 74);
VALUES(6258, 'Just a boy!  Not of the village. It was he who took it.  I never saw it again.  I swear on my life.', 195, 125, 74);
VALUES(6259, 'I believe you...', 195, 9, 74);
VALUES(6260, 'I thought it had stopped.', 195, 3, 74);
VALUES(6261, 'You can''t let him in, Harry. Dumbledore himself said it.  You have to close your mind.  It''s too dangerous --', 195, 3, 74);
VALUES(6262, 'It''s not a candle I can blow out, Hermione.  It always burns, even if it''s just a flicker.  Can you understand that?', 195, 1, 74);
VALUES(6263, 'Tell me. What you saw.', 195, 3, 74);
VALUES(6264, 'He''s found him.  Vol--', 195, 1, 74);
VALUES(6265, 'You-Know-Who.  He''s found Gregorovitch --', 195, 1, 74);
VALUES(6266, 'The wandmaker?', 195, 3, 74);
VALUES(6268, 'Viktor got his wand from Gregorovitch.  Most Durmstrang students did at one time.  What''s he got to do with You-Know-Who?', 195, 3, 74);
VALUES(6269, 'You-Know-Who wants something Gregorovitch once had -- dunno what.  But he''s desperate to have it.  It''s as if his life depends on it.', 195, 1, 74);
VALUES(6270, 'Don''t -- It... comforts him.', 195, 3, 74);
VALUES(6271, 'Well it sets my teeth on edge. What''s he expecting to hear?  Good news?', 195, 1, 74);
VALUES(6272, 'I think he just hopes he doesn''t hear bad news.  It gets him through the day.', 195, 3, 74);
VALUES(6273, 'And what gets you through the day?', 195, 1, 74);
VALUES(6274, 'We''ve all made sacrifices, Harry.', 195, 3, 74);
VALUES(6275, 'How long before he can travel?', 195, 1, 74);
VALUES(6276, 'I don''t know.  It takes time.  I''m doing all I can.', 195, 3, 74);
VALUES(6277, 'You''re not doing enough.', 195, 1, 74);
VALUES(6278, 'Take it off.', 195, 3, 74);
VALUES(6279, 'Take it off.  Now.', 195, 3, 74);
VALUES(6280, 'Better?', 195, 3, 74);
VALUES(6281, 'Loads.', 195, 1, 74);
VALUES(6282, 'It''s cold.  Even though it''s been lying against your skin for days.', 195, 3, 74);
VALUES(6283, 'We''ll take turns.  Okay?', 195, 3, 74);
VALUES(6284, 'What''s that?  That... smell?', 196, 53, 74);
VALUES(6285, 'Snatchers.', 196, 1, 74);
VALUES(6286, 'Good to know your enchantments work.', 196, 1, 74);
VALUES(6287, 'He could smell it.  My perfume.', 196, 3, 74);
VALUES(6288, 'We have to leave.  We''re not safe here.', 197, 1, 74);
VALUES(6289, 'I told you.  Ron''s not strong enough to Apparate.', 197, 3, 74);
VALUES(6290, 'Then we''ll go by foot.', 197, 1, 74);
VALUES(6291, 'I''m hungry.', 197, 2, 74);
VALUES(6292, 'We''re all hungry.', 197, 1, 74);
VALUES(6293, 'Leave it.', 197, 2, 74);
VALUES(6294, 'Mum can make food appear out of thin air.', 197, 2, 74);
VALUES(6295, 'No one can conjure food out of thin air.  Food is the first of the five Principal Exceptions to Gamp''s Law.  The other four are --', 197, 3, 74);
VALUES(6296, 'Oh, speak English, can''t you?', 197, 2, 74);
VALUES(6297, 'I said leave it.', 197, 2, 74);
VALUES(6298, 'It''ll be dark soon.  We need to find a place to sleep.', 197, 1, 74);
VALUES(6299, 'Good plan.', 197, 3, 74);
VALUES(6300, 'Yeah.  Brilliant.  Only, correct me if I''m wrong... wasn''t that yesterday''s plan?  And the day before that?  And the day before that?  Walk.  Sleep.  Walk. Sleep.', 197, 2, 74);
VALUES(6301, 'My turn.', 197, 1, 74);
VALUES(6302, 'He doesn''t know what he''s doing, does he?', 197, 2, 74);
VALUES(6303, 'None of us do.', 197, 3, 74);
VALUES(6304, 'Wizards were here.', 197, 2, 74);
VALUES(6305, 'I don''t like this place.', 197, 3, 74);
VALUES(6306, 'I want to go.', 197, 3, 74);
VALUES(6307, 'I''ll tell you in a minute.', 197, 3, 74);
VALUES(6308, 'Maybe you could tell me now.', 197, 1, 74);
VALUES(6309, 'Alright.  The Sword of Gryffindor? It''s Goblin made.', 197, 3, 74);
VALUES(6310, 'Brilliant.', 197, 1, 74);
VALUES(6311, 'You don''t understand.  Dirt and rust have no effect on the blade. It only takes in that which makes it stronger.', 197, 3, 74);
VALUES(6312, 'O-kay.', 197, 1, 74);
VALUES(6313, 'Harry.  You already destroyed one Horcrux, right?  Tom Riddle''s diary -- in the Chamber of Secrets.', 197, 3, 74);
VALUES(6314, 'With a basilisk fang.  If you tell me you''ve got one of those in that bloody beaded bag of yours --', 197, 1, 74);
VALUES(6315, 'Don''t you see!  In the Chamber of Secrets, you stabbed the basilisk with the Sword of Gryffindor.', 197, 3, 74);
VALUES(6316, 'Its blade is impregnated with basilisk venom.', 197, 3, 74);
VALUES(6317, 'It only takes in that which makes it stronger...', 197, 1, 74);
VALUES(6318, 'Exactly!  Which means...', 197, 3, 74);
VALUES(6319, '... it can destroy Horcruxes.', 197, 1, 74);
VALUES(6320, 'Which is why Dumbledore left it to you in his will.', 197, 3, 74);
VALUES(6321, 'You''re brilliant, Hermione. Truly.', 197, 1, 74);
VALUES(6322, 'Actually, I''m highly logical, which allows me to look past the extraneous detail and perceive clearly that which others overlook.', 197, 3, 74);
VALUES(6323, 'There''s only one problem...', 197, 1, 74);
VALUES(6324, 'The sword was stolen.', 197, 2, 74);
VALUES(6325, 'Yeah, I''m still here.  But you two carry on.  Don''t let me spoil your fun.', 197, 2, 74);
VALUES(6326, 'What''s the problem?', 197, 1, 74);
VALUES(6327, 'Problem?  There''s no problem.  Not according to you, anyway.', 197, 2, 74);
VALUES(6328, 'Look, don''t be shy.  If you''ve got something to say, spit it out.', 197, 1, 74);
VALUES(6329, 'All right, I''ll spit it out. Don''t expect me to skip up and down because now there''s some other damn thing we''ve got to find.', 197, 2, 74);
VALUES(6330, 'Ron...', 197, 3, 74);
VALUES(6331, 'I thought you knew what you signed up for.', 197, 1, 74);
VALUES(6332, 'Yeah, I thought I did too.', 197, 2, 74);
VALUES(6333, 'I don''t understand.  What part of this isn''t living up to your expectations?  Did you think we''d be staying in five-star hotels? Finding a Horcrux every other day? Did you think you''d be back to Mummy by Christmas?', 197, 1, 74);
VALUES(6334, 'No, I just reckoned after all this time, we''d have actually achieved something.  I reckoned you knew what you were doing.  I reckoned Dumbledore had told you something worthwhile! I reckoned you had a plan!', 197, 2, 74);
VALUES(6335, 'I''ve told you everything Dumbledore told me! And in case you haven''t noticed, we''ve found a Horcrux!', 197, 1, 74);
VALUES(6336, 'Yeah, and we''re about as near getting rid of it as we are to finding the rest of them, aren''t we!', 197, 2, 74);
VALUES(6337, 'Take it off, Ron.  Please take it off.  You wouldn''t be talking like this if you hadn''t been wearing it all day --', 197, 3, 74);
VALUES(6338, 'Yeah, he would.  D''you think I haven''t noticed the two of you whispering behind my back?  D''you think I haven''t guessed what you were thinking?', 197, 1, 74);
VALUES(6339, 'Harry, we weren''t --', 197, 3, 74);
VALUES(6340, 'Don''t lie!  You said it, too, you said you were disappointed --', 197, 2, 74);
VALUES(6341, 'I didn''t!  Not like that!  Harry -- I didn''t!', 197, 3, 74);
VALUES(6342, 'Do you know why I listen to that radio, every night?  Do you!  To make sure I don''t hear Ginny''s name or Fred or George or Mum or --', 197, 2, 74);
VALUES(6343, 'You think I don''t listen!  You think I don''t know what it''s like --', 197, 1, 74);
VALUES(6344, 'Stop!  Stop!', 197, 3, 74);
VALUES(6345, 'Go then.  But leave that.', 197, 1, 74);
VALUES(6346, 'And you?', 197, 2, 74);
VALUES(6347, 'Me?', 197, 3, 74);
VALUES(6348, 'Are you staying?  Or coming?', 197, 2, 74);
VALUES(6349, 'Fine.  I get it.  I saw you two the other night.  Yeah, that''s right.  Didn''t know I knew, did you?', 197, 2, 74);
VALUES(6350, 'What?  Ron, no -- please --', 197, 3, 74);
VALUES(6351, 'He''s gone.', 197, 3, 74);
VALUES(6352, 'Salvio Hexia... Protego Totalum...', 198, 1, 74);
VALUES(6353, 'It''s a Muggle station.', 198, 3, 74);
VALUES(6354, 'You were right.  It''s like you said.  Snitches have flesh memories.  But I didn''t catch my first Snitch with my hand.  I almost swallowed it.', 198, 1, 74);
VALUES(6355, '''I open at the close?''', 198, 3, 74);
VALUES(6356, 'What do you reckon it means?', 198, 1, 74);
VALUES(6357, 'I don''t know.  But look, I''ve found something as well...', 198, 3, 74);
VALUES(6358, 'I thought it was a picture of an eye, but now I don''t think it is. It isn''t a rune and it''s not in Spellman''s Syllabary either.  And it''s been inked in -- somebody drew it -- it isn''t part of the book.', 198, 3, 74);
VALUES(6359, 'Luna''s dad was wearing that, at Ron- At Bill and Fleur''s wedding.', 198, 1, 74);
VALUES(6360, 'What d''you mean -- wearing it?', 198, 3, 74);
VALUES(6361, 'Around his neck.  Like an amulet. I didn''t think much of it at the time.  You know Luna -- she''s always got some mad thing or the other she''s carrying around.  I just figured it ran in the family.', 198, 1, 74);
VALUES(6362, 'Why would someone have drawn it in a children''s book?', 198, 3, 74);
VALUES(6363, 'Hermione, I''ve been thinking.  I -- I want to go to Godric''s Hollow. It''s where I was born, it''s where my parents died --', 198, 1, 74);
VALUES(6364, 'And it''s exactly where You-Know- Who will expect you to go. Because it means something to you.', 198, 3, 74);
VALUES(6365, 'But it means something to him too, Hermione.  You-Know-Who nearly died there.  Wouldn''t that be just the kind of place he''d hide a Horcrux?', 198, 1, 74);
VALUES(6366, 'It''s dangerous, Harry.  But I have to admit, recently even I''ve been thinking we might have to go.  I think it''s possible something else is hidden there. The sword.  If Dumbledore didn''t want it falling into the Ministry''s hands, but wanted you to find it, what better place to hide it than the birthplace of the founder of Gryffindor himself?', 198, 3, 74);
VALUES(6367, 'Godric''s Hollow is the birthplace of Godric Gryffindor -- I mean, ''course it is.  Obvious, isn''t it?', 198, 1, 74);
VALUES(6368, 'Harry, did you ever even open A History of Magic?', 198, 3, 74);
VALUES(6369, 'Tossed it at Neville once when he was snoring -- might''ve popped open.', 198, 1, 74);
VALUES(6370, 'Hermione...', 198, 1, 74);
VALUES(6371, 'Don''t ever let me give you a haircut again.', 198, 3, 74);
VALUES(6372, 'I still think we should''ve used Polyjuice Potion.', 199, 3, 9);
VALUES(6373, 'No.  This is where I was born. I''m not returning as someone else.', 199, 1, 9);
VALUES(6374, 'Harry, I think it''s Christmas Eve! Listen...', 199, 3, 9);
VALUES(6375, 'Do you think they''d be in there? My mum and dad?', 199, 1, 9);
VALUES(6376, 'Yeah. I think they would.', 199, 3, 9);
VALUES(6377, 'Harry.', 199, 3, 9);
VALUES(6378, 'Is it -- ?', 199, 1, 9);
VALUES(6379, 'No.  But look.', 199, 3, 9);
VALUES(6380, 'Did you know he had a sister?', 199, 3, 9);
VALUES(6381, 'No.', 199, 1, 9);
VALUES(6382, 'Lumos.', 199, 3, 9);
VALUES(6383, 'Ignotus... Hey, Har --', 199, 3, 9);
VALUES(6384, 'Happy Christmas, Hermione.', 199, 1, 9);
VALUES(6385, 'Happy Christmas, Harry.', 199, 3, 9);
VALUES(6386, 'Harry...', 199, 3, 9);
VALUES(6387, 'Yeah.', 199, 1, 9);
VALUES(6388, 'Someone''s watching us.  By the gate.', 199, 3, 9);
VALUES(6389, 'C''mon.', 199, 1, 9);
VALUES(6390, 'I don''t think this is a good idea.', 199, 3, 9);
VALUES(6391, 'We look like ordinary Muggles.', 199, 1, 9);
VALUES(6392, 'Muggles who''ve just been laying flowers on your parents'' grave.', 199, 3, 9);
VALUES(6393, 'Relax.  This is right.  I know it.', 199, 1, 9);
VALUES(6394, 'Omigod.  Harry...', 199, 3, 9);
VALUES(6395, 'This is where they died, Hermione. This is where he murdered them.', 199, 1, 9);
VALUES(6396, 'You''re Bathilda, aren''t you?', 200, 1, 9);
VALUES(6397, 'Harry, I''m not sure about this.', 200, 3, 9);
VALUES(6398, 'Hermione, she knew Dumbledore. She might have the sword. Besides, she''s barely knee-high to a house-elf.  I think we can overpower her if it turns ugly.', 200, 1, 9);
VALUES(6399, 'There''s something odd about her. And what''s that smell?', 200, 3, 9);
VALUES(6400, 'She''s gaga, remember?', 200, 1, 9);
VALUES(6401, 'Here.  Let me do that.', 200, 1, 9);
VALUES(6402, 'You have a lovely house, Miss Bagshot.', 200, 3, 9);
VALUES(6403, 'Miss Bagshot?  Who is this man?', 200, 1, 9);
VALUES(6404, 'His name.  Can you tell me his name?', 200, 1, 9);
VALUES(6405, 'This is him, Hermione.  The one I saw in Gregorovitch''s wandshop. The thief.  Miss Bagshot, who is he?', 200, 1, 9);
VALUES(6406, 'She wants us to go upstairs.', 200, 1, 9);
VALUES(6407, 'All right...', 200, 3, 9);
VALUES(6408, 'She wants me to go.  Alone.', 200, 1, 9);
VALUES(6409, 'Why?', 200, 3, 9);
VALUES(6410, 'It''s all right.  You stay here.', 200, 1, 9);
VALUES(6411, 'Harry...', 200, 3, 9);
VALUES(6412, 'Lumos.', 200, 1, 9);
VALUES(6413, 'You are Potter?', 200, 104, 9);
VALUES(6414, 'Yes.', 200, 1, 9);
VALUES(6415, 'I have something for you...', 200, 104, 9);
VALUES(6416, 'Harry!', 200, 3, 9);
VALUES(6417, 'Confringo!', 200, 3, 9);
VALUES(6418, 'Harry... Harry, can you hear me...?', 200, 3, 68);
VALUES(6419, 'Yes.', 200, 1, 68);
VALUES(6420, 'Good.  That''s good...', 200, 3, 68);
VALUES(6421, 'We got away.', 200, 1, 68);
VALUES(6422, 'Yes.', 200, 3, 68);
VALUES(6423, 'Are you alright?', 200, 1, 68);
VALUES(6424, 'I''m fine.  But you''ve been sick. Rest... Rest a bit more...', 200, 3, 68);
VALUES(6425, 'You''ve outdone yourself this time.', 200, 1, 68);
VALUES(6426, 'The Forest of Dean.  I came here once with my mum and dad, years ago.  It''s just how I remember it. The trees.  The river.  It''s like nothing''s changed.  Not true, of course.  Everything''s changed.  If I brought my parents here, they wouldn''t recognize any of it.  Not the trees.  Not the river.  Not... me.', 200, 3, 68);
VALUES(6427, 'Where are they?', 200, 1, 68);
VALUES(6428, 'Wendell and Monica Wilkens now reside happily in Sydney, Australia.  They have two dogs, run a small sweet shop, but floss daily.  No children.', 200, 3, 68);
VALUES(6429, 'Maybe we should just stay here, Harry.  Grow old.', 200, 3, 68);
VALUES(6430, 'You wanted to know who the boy in the photograph was.  Well, I know.', 200, 3, 68);
VALUES(6674, 'Show me. Get Draco. Well?', 206, 22, 13);
VALUES(6431, 'It was in Bathilda''s sitting room. Rita Skeeter had sent it to her. Harry, it doesn''t make for very nice reading --', 200, 3, 68);
VALUES(6432, 'Who is he, Hermione?  The thief? Did Dumbledore know him?', 200, 1, 68);
VALUES(6433, 'Yes.', 200, 3, 68);
VALUES(6434, 'Well?', 200, 1, 68);
VALUES(6435, 'For a time.', 200, 3, 68);
VALUES(6436, 'Tell me, Hermione.  Who is he?', 200, 1, 68);
VALUES(6437, 'Gellert Grindelwald.  He''s not very well known in Britain, but there was a time, before You-Know- Who...', 200, 3, 68);
VALUES(6438, 'Hermione, I don''t need to have read A History of Magic to know who Gellert Grindelwald is.', 200, 1, 68);
VALUES(6439, 'When Grindelwald was seventeen, he was expelled from Durmstrang. He''d started doing some twisted things at school -- experiments. A few teachers had always protected him, but they couldn''t anymore.  After he left, he traveled for awhile, then ended up in Godric''s Hollow where his great aunt lived, Bathilda Bagshot.', 200, 3, 68);
VALUES(6440, 'Get to the hard part, Hermione.', 200, 1, 68);
VALUES(6441, 'She introduced him to Dumbledore. It made sense.  Dumbledore''s mother had just died, Grindelwald was troubled and they were both brilliant -- they''d never really had anyone they could talk to on the same level.  They did a lot of talking that summer.  But they always returned to one particular subject.', 200, 3, 68);
VALUES(6442, 'Wizard rule over Muggles.', 200, 3, 68);
VALUES(6443, 'And Dumbledore believed in it?', 200, 1, 68);
VALUES(6444, 'Yes.', 200, 3, 68);
VALUES(6445, '''For the Greater Good.''  What does that mean?', 200, 1, 68);
VALUES(6446, 'It was something Dumbledore came up with.  He believed wizards were superior and should rule over Muggles, but gently, for their own good.  Grindelwald took a more violent position.', 200, 3, 68);
VALUES(6447, 'It was a different time, Harry. It was one summer.  Dumbledore was young --', 200, 3, 68);
VALUES(6448, 'We''re young, Hermione.  And here we are, risking our lives to fight against the very thing Dumbledore supported.', 200, 1, 68);
VALUES(6449, 'He changed, Harry.  Years later, it was Dumbledore who put Grindelwald in prison.', 200, 3, 68);
VALUES(6450, 'Where''s my wand?  I''ll take the watch.', 200, 1, 68);
VALUES(6451, 'Hermione.  Where''s my wand?', 200, 1, 68);
VALUES(6452, 'It''s my fault.  As we were leaving Godric''s Hollow, I cast a curse and it rebounded... I''m sorry, Harry, I tried to mend it but wands are different --', 200, 3, 68);
VALUES(6453, 'It''s done.', 200, 1, 68);
VALUES(6454, 'Maybe we can --', 200, 3, 68);
VALUES(6455, 'It''s done.', 200, 1, 68);
VALUES(6456, 'Leave me yours.  You get back in the warm.  And give me that.', 201, 1, 68);
VALUES(6457, 'He loved you, Harry.  I know he loved you.', 201, 3, 68);
VALUES(6458, 'No...', 201, 1, 68);
VALUES(6459, 'Lumos! Accio Sword.', 201, 1, 68);
VALUES(6460, 'Diffindo.', 201, 1, 68);
VALUES(6461, 'Hermione...', 201, 1, 68);
VALUES(6462, 'Are -- you -- mental?', 201, 2, 68);
VALUES(6463, 'It was you!', 201, 1, 68);
VALUES(6464, 'Well, yeah.  Bit obvious, I''d think.', 201, 2, 68);
VALUES(6465, 'And the doe.  That was you as well.', 201, 1, 68);
VALUES(6466, 'No.  I reckoned it was you.', 201, 2, 68);
VALUES(6467, 'My Patronus is a stag.', 201, 1, 68);
VALUES(6468, 'Right.  Antlers.', 201, 2, 68);
VALUES(6469, 'You didn''t see anyone else?', 201, 1, 68);
VALUES(6470, 'No, I... I did think maybe I saw something -- when I was running -- over there --', 201, 2, 68);
VALUES(6471, 'Anything?', 201, 2, 68);
VALUES(6472, 'But I reckon whoever cast the doe, put the sword in that pool hoping we''d find it.', 201, 1, 68);
VALUES(6473, 'And we did, didn''t we?', 201, 2, 68);
VALUES(6474, 'See that?  It knows.  It''s afraid. Do it.', 201, 1, 68);
VALUES(6475, 'What?  No.  Harry.  That thing''s bad for me.  I can''t handle it. I''m not making excuses for how I acted, but that thing affects me more than it affects you and Hermione.  It made me think stuff -- stuff I was thinking anyway, but it made everything worse.', 201, 2, 68);
VALUES(6476, 'All the more reason.', 201, 1, 68);
VALUES(6477, 'No.  I can''t --', 201, 2, 68);
VALUES(6478, 'Then why are you here?  Why did you come back?', 201, 1, 68);
VALUES(6479, 'I''ll have to speak to it in order for it to open.  When it does, don''t hesitate.  I don''t know what''s in here, but it''ll put up a fight.  The bit of Riddle that was in his diary tried to kill me.', 201, 1, 68);
VALUES(6480, 'On three.  One.  Two.  Three. Take me inside...', 201, 1, 68);
VALUES(6481, 'Stab it, Ron.  Now.', 201, 1, 68);
VALUES(6482, 'I have seen your heart and it is mine...', 201, 9, 68);
VALUES(6483, 'Don''t listen to it.', 201, 1, 68);
VALUES(6484, 'Ron.  Don''t listen to it!', 201, 1, 68);
VALUES(6485, 'Ron.  Stab it!', 201, 1, 68);
VALUES(6486, 'We were better without you, happier without you.', 201, 1, 68);
VALUES(6487, 'Who could look at you beside Harry Potter?  What are you, compared with the Chosen One...?', 201, 3, 68);
VALUES(6488, 'Ron.  It lies!  Stab it!  STAB IT!', 201, 1, 68);
VALUES(6489, 'Your mother confessed that she would have preferred me as a son...', 201, 1, 68);
VALUES(6490, 'Who wouldn''t prefer him, what woman would take you, you are nothing, nothing, nothing to him...', 201, 3, 68);
VALUES(6491, 'Do it, Ron!  Kill it!', 201, 1, 68);
VALUES(6492, 'After you left, she cried for a week.  She''s like my sister.', 201, 1, 68);
VALUES(6493, 'I''m sorry.  I''m sorry I left.', 201, 2, 68);
VALUES(6494, 'You''ve sort of made up for it tonight.  Getting the sword. Finishing off the Horcrux.', 201, 1, 68);
VALUES(6495, 'Saving your life.', 201, 2, 68);
VALUES(6496, 'That too.', 201, 1, 68);
VALUES(6497, 'And just think of it.  Only three to go.', 201, 2, 68);
VALUES(6498, 'Hermione!', 201, 1, 68);
VALUES(6499, 'Everything all right?', 201, 3, 68);
VALUES(6500, 'Fine.  Actually... more than fine.', 201, 1, 68);
VALUES(6501, 'Hey.', 201, 2, 68);
VALUES(6502, 'Wo -- hey -- ouch!', 201, 2, 68);
VALUES(6503, 'You -- complete -- arse -- Ronald -- Weasley!  You crawl back here after all these weeks and say, ''Hey?'' Where''s my wand?  Harry, where''s my wand!', 201, 3, 68);
VALUES(6504, 'Um... I don''t know?', 201, 1, 68);
VALUES(6505, 'Harry Potter, you give me my wand!', 201, 3, 68);
VALUES(6506, 'How come he''s got your wand?', 201, 2, 68);
VALUES(6507, 'Never mind why he''s got my wand --', 201, 3, 68);
VALUES(6508, 'What is that?', 201, 3, 68);
VALUES(6509, 'You destroyed it?', 201, 3, 68);
VALUES(6510, 'It''s a long story.', 201, 1, 68);
VALUES(6511, 'Don''t think this changes anything.', 201, 3, 68);
VALUES(6512, 'No, of course not.  I only destroyed a bloody freaking Horcrux!  Why would that change anything!  Do you know what it was like for me to hear those words coming from you!  To see you doing those things --', 201, 2, 68);
VALUES(6513, 'See me doing what things?', 201, 3, 68);
VALUES(6514, 'What happened out there?', 201, 3, 68);
VALUES(6515, 'It''s a long story.', 201, 1, 68);
VALUES(6516, 'Look, I wanted to come back the minute I''d left.  I just... didn''t know how to find you.', 202, 2, 68);
VALUES(6517, 'Exactly how did you find us?', 202, 1, 68);
VALUES(6518, 'With this.', 202, 2, 68);
VALUES(6519, 'It doesn''t just turn off lights. I don''t know exactly how it works, but Christmas morning I -- I was sleeping -- in this little pub-- I''d given some Snatchers the slip the night before, me being a blood- traitor and all -- anyway, I was sleeping when I heard it...', 202, 2, 68);
VALUES(6520, 'It?', 202, 1, 68);
VALUES(6521, 'A voice.', 202, 2, 68);
VALUES(6522, 'Your voice, Hermione.  Coming out of this.', 202, 2, 68);
VALUES(6523, 'And what may I ask did I say?', 202, 3, 68);
VALUES(6524, 'My name.  Just my name.  Like a whisper.', 202, 2, 68);
VALUES(6525, 'So I took this and I clicked it and this tiny ball of light appeared.  And I knew.', 202, 2, 68);
VALUES(6526, 'Knew what?', 202, 1, 68);
VALUES(6527, 'Just knew.  On account of Hermione''s voice.  And sure enough, it floated toward me, the ball of light, right to my chest and then -- went straight through -- right here.', 202, 2, 68);
VALUES(6528, 'I could feel it inside me.  It was warm, like the first sip of a good cup of tea.  And I knew it would take me where I needed to go.', 202, 2, 68);
VALUES(6529, 'So I Disapparated and came out on this hillside.  It was dark.  I didn''t have any idea where I was. I just had to hope one of you would show yourselves in the end. And you did.', 202, 2, 68);
VALUES(6530, 'I''ve always liked it.  These flames Hermione makes.', 202, 2, 68);
VALUES(6531, 'How long you reckon she''ll stay mad at me?', 202, 2, 68);
VALUES(6532, 'Keep talking ''bout that little ball of light touching your heart -- she''ll come round.', 202, 1, 68);
VALUES(6533, 'It was true.  Every word.', 202, 2, 68);
VALUES(6534, 'Bloody hell.  I just realized. You need a wand, right?', 202, 2, 68);
VALUES(6535, 'Yeah...', 202, 1, 68);
VALUES(6536, 'Well, I''ve got one.  Here.  It''s Blackthorn, ten inches, nothing special, but I reckon it''ll do.  I took it off a Snatcher a few weeks back.', 202, 2, 68);
VALUES(6537, 'Don''t tell Hermione, but they''re a bit dim, Snatchers.  This one was definitely part Troll.  The smell off him...', 202, 2, 68);
VALUES(6538, 'Engorgio.', 202, 1, 68);
VALUES(6539, 'Wo.', 202, 2, 68);
VALUES(6540, 'Reducio!', 202, 1, 68);
VALUES(6541, 'What''s going on in there?', 202, 3, 68);
VALUES(6542, 'Nothing.', 202, 1, 68);
VALUES(6543, 'Nothing.', 202, 2, 68);
VALUES(6544, 'Maybe a bit more practice, eh?', 202, 2, 68);
VALUES(6545, 'We need to talk.', 202, 3, 68);
VALUES(6546, 'All right.', 202, 2, 68);
VALUES(6547, 'I want to go and see Xenophilius Lovegood.', 202, 3, 68);
VALUES(6548, 'Sorry?', 202, 1, 68);
VALUES(6549, 'See this?  It''s a letter Dumbledore wrote to Grindelwald. Look at the signature.  It''s the mark again.', 202, 3, 68);
VALUES(6550, 'It keeps cropping up.  Here.  In Beedle the Bard.  In the graveyard in Godric''s Hollow -- what?', 202, 3, 68);
VALUES(6551, 'Jesus.  It was there too.', 202, 1, 68);
VALUES(6552, 'Where?', 202, 3, 68);
VALUES(6553, 'Outside Gregorovitch''s wand shop. on the alley wall...', 202, 1, 68);
VALUES(6554, 'But what does it mean?', 202, 2, 68);
VALUES(6555, 'Harry, you don''t have a clue where the next Horcrux is.  And neither do I.  But this, this means something.  I''m sure of it.', 202, 3, 68);
VALUES(6556, 'I think Hermione''s right.  I think we ought to go and see Lovegood. What say we vote on it?  Those in favor...', 202, 2, 68);
VALUES(6557, 'Sorry, Harry.  Looks like it''s Hermione and me this time.', 202, 2, 68);
VALUES(6558, 'Not still mad at him, are you?', 202, 1, 68);
VALUES(6559, 'I''m always mad at him.', 202, 3, 68);
VALUES(6560, 'Luna?', 203, 2, 12);
VALUES(6561, 'Luna.', 203, 1, 12);
VALUES(6562, 'Luna.', 203, 3, 12);
VALUES(6563, 'Keep off the dirigible plums.', 203, 2, 12);
VALUES(6564, 'What is it? Who are you? What do you want --', 203, 34, 12);
VALUES(6565, 'Hello, Mr. Lovegood.  I''m Harry Potter.  We met a few months back?', 203, 1, 12);
VALUES(6566, 'Would it be okay if we came in? It won''t take long, sir.  I promise.', 203, 1, 12);
VALUES(6567, 'Excuse me.', 203, 34, 12);
VALUES(6568, 'So.  What brings you here, Mr. Potter?', 203, 34, 12);
VALUES(6569, 'Well, sir, we need some help.', 203, 1, 12);
VALUES(6570, 'Ah.  Help.  I see.  Yes, well, the thing is, helping Harry Potter, rather dangerous these days...', 203, 34, 12);
VALUES(6571, 'Aren''t you the one who keeps telling everyone it''s their first duty to help Harry?', 203, 2, 12);
VALUES(6572, 'I have expressed that view, yes. In the past.  Would you excuse me one moment.  I shall return shortly and, um, try to help you...', 203, 34, 12);
VALUES(6573, 'What''s going on here?', 203, 1, 12);
VALUES(6574, 'He''s mental.  Let''s face it. Luna''s always good value, but she''s nutty as squirrel poo.', 203, 2, 12);
VALUES(6575, 'Do you see that?', 203, 3, 12);
VALUES(6576, 'Well, yeah, of course.  It''s massive, isn''t it?', 203, 2, 12);
VALUES(6577, 'No!  Don''t go near it!', 203, 3, 12);
VALUES(6578, 'It''s an Erumpent horn.  It''s a Class B Tradeable Material.', 203, 3, 12);
VALUES(6579, 'Yeah, all right...', 203, 2, 12);
VALUES(6580, 'May I offer you all an infusion of Gurdyroots? We make it ourselves.', 203, 34, 12);
VALUES(6581, 'Where is Luna, sir?', 203, 3, 12);
VALUES(6582, 'Luna?  Oh, um, she''ll be along. Now how can I help you, Mr. Potter?', 203, 34, 12);
VALUES(6583, 'Well, sir, it''s about something you were wearing around your neck at the wedding.  A symbol...', 203, 1, 12);
VALUES(6584, 'You mean this?', 203, 34, 12);
VALUES(6585, 'Yes!  Exactly.  What we wondered, sir, is, well, what is it?', 203, 1, 12);
VALUES(6586, 'What is it?  Well, it''s the sign of the Deathly Hallows, of course.', 203, 34, 12);
VALUES(6587, 'The what?', 203, 1, 12);
VALUES(6588, 'The what?', 203, 2, 12);
VALUES(6589, 'The what?', 203, 3, 12);
VALUES(6590, 'The Deathly Hallows.  I assume you''re all familiar with ''The Tale of the Three Brothers?''', 203, 34, 12);
VALUES(6591, 'Yes.', 203, 3, 12);
VALUES(6592, 'Yes.', 203, 2, 12);
VALUES(6593, 'No.', 203, 1, 12);
VALUES(6594, 'It''s in here.', 203, 3, 12);
VALUES(6595, 'Well, there''s no real reason to go on unless one is familiar with the tale.  Why don''t you read it aloud, Miss...?', 203, 34, 12);
VALUES(6596, 'Granger.  Well... all right. There were once three brothers who were traveling along a lonely, winding road at twilight --', 203, 3, 12);
VALUES(6597, 'Midnight.  Mum always said midnight. But twilight''s fine.  Better actually.', 203, 2, 12);
VALUES(6598, 'In time, the brothers reached a river too treacherous to pass...', 203, 3, 12);
VALUES(6599, 'Well, there you are.  Those are the Deathly Hallows.', 203, 34, 12);
VALUES(6600, 'Sorry... I still don''t really understand...', 203, 1, 12);
VALUES(6601, 'The Elder Wand...', 203, 34, 12);
VALUES(6602, 'The Resurrection Stone...', 203, 34, 12);
VALUES(6603, '... then encloses both in a TRIANGLE. The Cloak of Invisibility. Together... they make the Deathly Hallows.  Together... they make one master of Death.', 203, 34, 12);
VALUES(6604, 'Mr. Lovegood, does the Peverell family have anything to do with the Deathly Hallows?', 203, 3, 12);
VALUES(6605, 'Ignotus and his brothers Cadmus and Antioch are thought to be the original owners of the Hallows and therefore the inspiration for the story.', 203, 34, 12);
VALUES(6606, 'Ah, but your tea''s grown cold. Excuse me, I''ll be right back.', 203, 34, 12);
VALUES(6607, 'Let''s get out of here once he''s back.  I''m not touching this stuff, hot or cold.', 204, 2, 12);
VALUES(6608, 'Which one would you choose if you could?  Of the Deathly Hallows?', 204, 1, 12);
VALUES(6609, 'It''s obvious, isn''t it?', 204, 3, 12);
VALUES(6610, 'The Wand.', 204, 2, 12);
VALUES(6611, 'The Cloak.', 204, 3, 12);
VALUES(6612, 'The Stone.', 204, 1, 12);
VALUES(6613, 'You''re supposed to say the Cloak, but who wants to spend all day being invisible.  Dead boring if you ask me.  But an unbeatable wand!', 204, 2, 12);
VALUES(6614, 'Its owner grew drunk with power and was murdered.', 204, 3, 12);
VALUES(6615, 'Yeah, but imagine what a short wicked life you''d lead.', 204, 2, 12);
VALUES(6616, 'Why the Stone, Harry?', 204, 3, 12);
VALUES(6617, 'Well, you could bring people back, couldn''t you?  Mad-Eye. Dumbledore.  Sirius.  Anybody.', 204, 1, 12);
VALUES(6618, 'But according to the story they don''t want to come back.  It''s all rubbish anyway.  There''s no such thing as the Deathly Hallows.', 204, 3, 12);
VALUES(6619, 'But I have one.  The Invisibility Cloak my father left me.', 204, 1, 12);
VALUES(6620, 'There have always been Cloaks --', 204, 3, 12);
VALUES(6621, 'Not like Harry''s.  I''ve seen a fair few.  Dad used to bring home the ones the Ministry confiscated from petty thieves and the like. They always got holes or tears. Harry''s is different.  It''s perfect.', 204, 2, 12);
VALUES(6622, 'And I think I''ve actually held the Resurrection Stone in my hands, that night in Dumbledore''s office when he showed me the ring he''d destroyed, the Horcrux.  It had a symbol on it.  Now I think it was the mark of the Hallows.', 204, 1, 12);
VALUES(6623, 'Mr. Lovegood.  Thank you, sir --', 204, 3, 12);
VALUES(6624, 'You forgot the water.', 204, 2, 12);
VALUES(6625, 'The water?', 204, 34, 12);
VALUES(6626, 'For the tea.', 204, 2, 12);
VALUES(6627, 'Did, didn''t I?  How silly of me.', 204, 34, 12);
VALUES(6628, 'No matter, sir.  We really ought to be go--', 204, 3, 12);
VALUES(6629, 'No, you mustn''t --', 204, 34, 12);
VALUES(6630, 'Sir?', 204, 1, 12);
VALUES(6631, 'You''re my only hope.  They were angry, you see, about what I''d been writing, so they took her. They took my Luna... But it''s really you they want...', 204, 34, 12);
VALUES(6632, 'Who took her, sir?', 204, 1, 12);
VALUES(6633, 'Him.  Surely you call him You-Know- Who.  But his real name of course is... Voldemort.', 204, 34, 12);
VALUES(6634, 'Nooooooooo!', 204, 2, 12);
VALUES(6635, 'Stop!  I''ve got him --', 204, 34, 12);
VALUES(6636, 'Ron!  Harry!  Take my hand!', 204, 3, 12);
VALUES(6637, 'That treacherous old bleeder!  Is there no one we can trust!', 204, 2, 68);
VALUES(6638, 'They''ve kidnapped Luna because he supported me.  He was just desperate.', 204, 1, 68);
VALUES(6639, 'I''ll do the enchantments.', 204, 2, 68);
VALUES(6640, 'Hello, beautiful.', 204, 53, 68);
VALUES(6641, 'Ah, Tom, I thought you would come one day.  But surely you must know I no longer have what you seek...', 204, 98, 68);
VALUES(6642, 'If not you, then who?', 204, 9, 68);
VALUES(6643, 'You''re so innocent, Tom.  Like a schoolboy.  There''s so much you don''t understand...', 204, 98, 68);
VALUES(6644, 'Tell me, Grindelwald.  Tell me where to find it!  Tell me who possesses it!  The name, Grindelwald!  The name!', 204, 9, 68);
VALUES(6645, 'Can''t you guess, Tom?  It lies with him, of course.  Buried within the earth.  It is he who possesses it, even in death.  Your old friend and mine... Dumbledore.', 204, 98, 68);
VALUES(6646, 'They exist.  The Hallows.', 204, 1, 68);
VALUES(6647, 'But he only wants the one, the last one.  That''s what he''s been looking for.', 204, 1, 68);
VALUES(6648, 'What''re you saying?', 204, 3, 68);
VALUES(6649, 'He knows where it is, You-Know- Who.  He''ll have it by the end of the night.  He''s found the Elder Wand.', 204, 1, 68);
VALUES(6650, 'Don''t touch her!', 205, 2, 68);
VALUES(6651, 'Stop it!', 205, 3, 68);
VALUES(6652, 'Your boyfriend''ll get worse than that if he doesn''t behave, lovely.', 205, 53, 68);
VALUES(6653, 'What happened to you, ugly?', 205, 53, 68);
VALUES(6654, 'What''s your name?', 205, 53, 68);
VALUES(6655, 'Dudely.  Vernon Dudley.', 205, 1, 68);
VALUES(6656, 'Check the list.  And you, ginger?', 205, 53, 68);
VALUES(6657, 'Stan Shunpike.', 205, 2, 68);
VALUES(6658, 'Like ''ell you are.  We know skinny Stan.  Try again.', 205, 53, 68);
VALUES(6659, 'Weasley... Barney Weasley.', 205, 2, 68);
VALUES(6660, 'Weasley, eh?  Wouldn''t be related to that blood traitor Arthur Weasley, would you?', 205, 53, 68);
VALUES(6661, 'Piss off!  Arthur Weasley''s ten times the wizard you are!', 205, 2, 68);
VALUES(6662, 'Worth ten times you if I can find him.  Wasn''t you that tipped him off, was it?', 205, 53, 68);
VALUES(6663, 'How ''bout you, lovely?  What do they call you...?', 205, 53, 68);
VALUES(6664, 'Penelope Clearwater.  Half-blood.', 205, 3, 68);
VALUES(6665, 'You smell like vanilla, Penelope. I think you''re going to be my favorite.', 205, 53, 68);
VALUES(6666, 'There''s no Vernon Dudley on ''ere.', 205, 145, 68);
VALUES(6667, 'Hear that, ugly?  The list says you''re lying.  How come you don''t want us to know who you are?  Hm?', 205, 102, 68);
VALUES(6668, 'The list is wrong.  I told you who I am --', 205, 1, 68);
VALUES(6669, 'Change of plans, boys.  We won''t be taking this lot to the Ministry.', 205, 53, 68);
VALUES(6675, 'I can''t be sure.', 206, 12, 13);
VALUES(6676, 'Draco. Look closely, son. If we are the ones to hand Potter over to the Dark Lord... ...everything would be forgiven. All would be as it was, you understand?', 206, 23, 13);
VALUES(6677, 'Now, we won''t be forgetting who actually caught him, I hope, Mr. Malfoy.', 206, 53, 13);
VALUES(6678, 'You dare to talk to me like that in my own house?', 206, 23, 13);
VALUES(6679, 'Lucius. Don''t be shy, sweetie. Come over. Now, if this isn''t who we think it is, Draco, and we call him, he''ll kill us all. We need to be absolutely sure.', 206, 22, 13);
VALUES(6680, 'What''s wrong with his face?', 206, 12, 13);
VALUES(6681, 'Yes, what is wrong with his face?', 206, 22, 13);
VALUES(6682, 'He came to us like that. Something he picked up in the forest, I reckon.', 206, 145, 13);
VALUES(6683, 'Or ran into a Stinging Jinx. Was it you, dearie? Give me her wand. We''ll see what her last spell was. Ah. Got you. What is that? Where''d you get that from?', 206, 22, 13);
VALUES(6684, 'It was in her bag when we searched her. Reckon it''s mine now. Are you mad? Go! Get out!', 206, 145, 13);
VALUES(6685, 'Cissy, put the boys in the cellar. I want to have a little conversation with this one, girl-to-girl.', 206, 22, 13);
VALUES(6686, 'What are we gonna do? We can''t leave Hermione alone with her.', 206, 2, 13);
VALUES(6687, 'Ron? Harry?', 206, 25, 13);
VALUES(6688, 'Luna?', 206, 1, 13);
VALUES(6689, 'That sword is meant to be in my vault at Gringotts. How did you get it? What else did you and your friends take from my vault?!', 206, 22, 13);
VALUES(6690, 'I didn''t take anything. Please. I didn''t take anything.', 206, 3, 13);
VALUES(6691, 'I don''t believe it.', 206, 22, 13);
VALUES(6692, 'We have to do something.', 206, 2, 13);
VALUES(6693, 'There''s no way out of here. We''ve tried everything. It''s enchanted.', 206, 43, 13);
VALUES(6694, 'Please! please!', 206, 3, 13);
VALUES(6695, 'Shut up!', 206, 22, 13);
VALUES(6696, 'You''re bleeding, Harry. That''s a curious thing to keep in your sock.', 206, 25, 13);
VALUES(6697, 'Help us.', 206, 1, 13);
VALUES(6698, 'Let her go.', 206, 2, 13);
VALUES(6699, 'Shut up. Get back. You, goblin, come with me.', 206, 44, 13);
VALUES(6700, 'Aah!', 207, 27, 13);
VALUES(6701, 'Dobby? What are you doing here?', 207, 1, 13);
VALUES(6702, 'Dobby has come to rescue Harry Potter, of course. Dobby will always be there for Harry Potter.', 207, 27, 13);
VALUES(6703, 'You can Apparate in and out of this room? Could you take us with you?', 207, 1, 13);
VALUES(6704, 'Of course, sir. I''m an elf.', 207, 27, 13);
VALUES(6705, 'Works for me.', 207, 2, 13);
VALUES(6706, 'Dobby, I want you to take Luna and Mr. Ollivander--', 207, 1, 13);
VALUES(6707, 'Shell Cottage on the outskirts of Tinworth. Trust me.', 207, 2, 13);
VALUES(6708, 'Whenever you''re ready, sir.', 207, 25, 13);
VALUES(6709, 'Sir? I like her very much. Meet me at the top of the stairs in 10 seconds.', 207, 27, 13);
VALUES(6710, 'Ow.', 207, 44, 13);
VALUES(6711, 'Who gets his wand?', 207, 27, 13);
VALUES(6712, 'I''m only going to ask you once more, goblin. Think very, very carefully before you answer.', 207, 22, 13);
VALUES(6713, 'I don''t know.', 207, 30, 13);
VALUES(6714, 'You don''t know? Why weren''t you doing your job? Who got into my vault? Who stole it? Who stole it? Well?', 207, 22, 13);
VALUES(6715, 'When I was last in your vault, the sword was there. Oh, well then, perhaps it just walked out on its own then.', 207, 30, 13);
VALUES(6716, 'There is no place safer than Gringotts.', 207, 30, 13);
VALUES(6717, 'Liar! Consider yourself lucky, goblin. The same won''t be said for this one.', 207, 22, 13);
VALUES(6718, 'Like hell.', 207, 2, 13);
VALUES(6719, 'Expellliarmus!', 207, 2, 13);
VALUES(6720, 'Stupefy.', 207, 1, 13);
VALUES(6721, 'Stop! Drop your wands. I said, drop them! Pick them up, Draco, now. Well, well, well, look what we have here. It''s Harry Potter. He''s all bright and shiny and new again, just in time for the Dark Lord. Call him. Call him.', 207, 22, 13);
VALUES(6722, 'Stupefy!', 207, 1, 13);
VALUES(6723, 'Stupid elf. You could''ve killed me.', 207, 22, 13);
VALUES(6724, 'Dobby never meant to kill. Dobby only meant to maim or seriously injure.', 207, 27, 13);
VALUES(6725, 'How dare you take a witch''s wand? How dare you defy your masters?', 207, 22, 13);
VALUES(6726, 'Dobby has no master. Dobby is a free elf. And Dobby has come to save Harry Potter and his friends.', 207, 27, 13);
VALUES(6727, 'Hermione. You''re all right. We''re safe. We''re all safe.', 208, 1, 15);
VALUES(6728, 'Harry Potter.', 208, 27, 15);
VALUES(6729, 'Dobby. Dobby. No, just-- Hold on. Hold on. Look, just hold on, okay? We''ll fix you. Hermione will have something. In your bag. Hermione? Hermione? What is it? Help me.', 208, 1, 15);
VALUES(6730, 'Such a beautiful place... ...to be with friends. Dobby is happy to be with his friend... ...Harry Potter.', 208, 27, 15);
VALUES(6731, 'We should close his eyes. Don''t you think? There. Now he could be sleeping.', 208, 25, 15);
VALUES(6732, 'I want to bury him. Properly. Without magic.', 208, 1, 15);
VALUES(6733, 'It''s beautiful here.', 209, 25, 15);
VALUES(6734, 'It was our Aunt''s. We used to come here as kids. The Order uses it now as a safe house -- what''s left of us, at least.', 209, 73, 15);
VALUES(6735, 'Muggles think these keep evil away. But they''re wrong...', 209, 25, 15);
VALUES(6736, 'I need to talk to the goblin.', 209, 1, 15);
VALUES(6737, 'How are you?', 210, 1, 15);
VALUES(6738, 'Alive.', 210, 30, 15);
VALUES(6739, 'You probably don''t remember --', 210, 1, 15);
VALUES(6740, 'Yes.', 210, 1, 15);
VALUES(6741, 'And brought me here.', 210, 30, 15);
VALUES(6742, 'You are a very unusual wizard.', 210, 30, 15);
VALUES(6743, 'Why did you leave Gringotts?', 210, 1, 15);
VALUES(6744, 'Soon the Death Eaters will control it. That was unacceptable to me.', 210, 30, 15);
VALUES(6745, 'Then you''re on our side.', 210, 2, 15);
VALUES(6746, 'This is a wizard''s war. I take no side.', 210, 30, 15);
VALUES(6747, 'It is impossible.', 210, 30, 15);
VALUES(6748, 'Alone, yes. With you, no.', 210, 1, 15);
VALUES(6749, 'How did you come by this sword?', 210, 30, 15);
VALUES(6750, 'It''s complicated. Why did Bellatrix Lestrange think it should be in her vault at Gringotts?', 210, 1, 15);
VALUES(6751, 'It''s complicated.', 210, 30, 15);
VALUES(6752, 'The sword presented itself to us in a moment of need. We didn''t steal it.', 210, 1, 15);
VALUES(6753, 'There is a sword in Madam Lestrange''s vault identical to this one, but it is a fake. It was placed there this past summer.', 210, 30, 15);
VALUES(6754, 'And she never suspected?', 210, 1, 15);
VALUES(6755, 'The replica is very convincing. Only a goblin would recognize that this is the true Sword of Gryffindor.', 210, 30, 15);
VALUES(6756, 'Who put it there? The fake.', 210, 2, 15);
VALUES(6757, 'It was not my place to ask, nor did I desire to. There are more than a few curious things in the vaults at Gringotts.', 210, 30, 15);
VALUES(6758, 'And in Madam Lestrange''s vault as well?', 210, 1, 15);
VALUES(6759, 'Perhaps.', 210, 30, 15);
VALUES(6760, 'I have no interest in gold.', 210, 30, 15);
VALUES(6761, 'Then what? The goblin twists the curl at his chin... then his eyes', 210, 1, 15);
VALUES(6762, 'That is my price.', 210, 30, 15);
VALUES(6763, 'I have your word, Harry Potter, that you will give me the Sword of Gryffindor if I help you?', 210, 30, 15);
VALUES(6764, 'Harry, are you thinking there''s a Horcrux in Bellatrix''s vault?', 210, 3, 15);
VALUES(6765, 'She was terrified when she thought we''d been in there. She kept asking you what else we''d taken. I''d bet anything there''s a Horcrux there. If we find it, we can kill it. And if we kill it, we''re one step closer to killing him.', 210, 1, 15);
VALUES(6766, 'And if we find one? How''re we supposed to destroy it if we''ve given Griphook the sword?', 210, 2, 15);
VALUES(6767, 'I''m still working on that part.', 210, 1, 15);
VALUES(6768, 'He''s too weak.', 211, 81, 15);
VALUES(6769, 'Forgive me if I don''t get up.', 211, 43, 15);
VALUES(6770, 'Mr. Ollivander, I need to ask you a few questions.', 211, 1, 15);
VALUES(6771, 'Anything, m''boy, anything.', 211, 43, 15);
VALUES(6772, 'Can you identify these, sir?', 211, 1, 15);
VALUES(6773, 'Walnut and dragon heartstring. Twelve and three quarter inches. Unyielding. This belongs to Bellatrix Lestrange.', 211, 43, 15);
VALUES(6774, 'And this?', 211, 1, 15);
VALUES(6775, 'Hawthorn. Unicorn hair. Ten inches. Reasonably pliant. This was the wand of Draco Malfoy.', 211, 43, 15);
VALUES(6776, 'Was? Isn''t it still?', 211, 1, 15);
VALUES(6777, 'Perhaps not -- if you won it from him. I sense its allegiance has changed.', 211, 43, 15);
VALUES(6778, 'The wand chooses the wizard, Mr. Potter. That much has always been clear to those of us who have studied wandlore.', 211, 43, 15);
VALUES(6779, 'What do you know about the Deathly Hallows, sir?', 211, 1, 15);
VALUES(6780, 'There are rumored to be three: The Elder Wand, the Resurrection Stone and the Invisibility Cloak. It is said that to possess them all is to make oneself the Master of Death. But few truly believe such objects exist --', 211, 43, 15);
VALUES(6781, 'But you, sir? Do you believe they exist?', 211, 1, 15);
VALUES(6782, 'You''re lying. You know one exists and you told him about it. You told him about the Elder Wand and where to go looking for it.', 211, 1, 15);
VALUES(6783, 'He tortured me! Besides, I conveyed only rumors. There''s no guarantee he will find it --', 211, 43, 15);
VALUES(6784, 'He has found it, sir.', 211, 1, 15);
VALUES(6785, 'That''s all, sir. We''ll leave you to get some rest now.', 211, 1, 15);
VALUES(6786, 'He''s after you, Mr. Potter. If it''s true, what you say, that he has the Elder Wand, I''m afraid you really don''t stand a chance.', 211, 43, 15);
VALUES(6787, 'Then I guess I''ll just have to kill him before he finds me, sir.', 211, 1, 15);
VALUES(6788, 'You''re sure it''s hers?', 211, 2, 15);
VALUES(6789, 'Positive. Harry turns to the two wands on the table -- the ones he showed Ollivander -- and extends the longest to Hermione.', 211, 3, 15);
VALUES(6790, 'I reckon you should take this then.', 211, 1, 15);
VALUES(6791, 'You heard Ollivander. It''s Harry''s now.', 211, 2, 15);
VALUES(6792, 'But I hate that thing -- that''s the wand that killed Sirius! How can I hold it and not feel...', 211, 3, 15);
VALUES(6793, 'If I can hold it, you can.', 211, 1, 15);
VALUES(6794, 'How will we know what it is when we get in there? After all, a Horcrux can be anything.', 211, 2, 15);
VALUES(6795, 'I''ll know. I can''t explain. It''s like...', 211, 1, 15);
VALUES(6796, 'That''s a bit scary.', 211, 2, 15);
VALUES(6797, 'It is, Harry. Did Dumbledore ever say anything to you, something that might explain why --', 211, 3, 15);
VALUES(6798, 'No. I just know. When one''s near.', 211, 1, 15);
VALUES(6799, 'This is the closest I could find to what you described, Hermione.', 211, 81, 15);
VALUES(6800, 'It''s perfect. Thank you, Fleur.', 211, 3, 15);
VALUES(6801, 'You''re leaving, aren''t you.', 211, 73, 15);
VALUES(6802, 'In the morning.', 211, 1, 15);
VALUES(6803, 'And Griphook?', 211, 73, 15);
VALUES(6804, 'He''ll be leaving too.', 211, 1, 15);
VALUES(6805, 'Listen, I don''t know what you''re up to, but I know goblins. If you''ve struck any kind of bargain with Griphook, you must be exceptionally careful to live up to it. If you don''t... he won''t be forgiving.', 211, 73, 15);
VALUES(6806, 'The sky has lost a star.', 211, 25, 15);
VALUES(6807, 'My father used to say that when a child died. She looks up, smiles.', 211, 25, 15);
VALUES(6808, 'Yeah. Funny. Listen, Luna, about your father, I don''t want you to think I --', 211, 1, 15);
VALUES(6809, 'I know you understand why my father did what he did, Harry. That''s why we don''t need to talk about it.', 211, 25, 15);
VALUES(6810, 'Hogwarts?', 211, 1, 15);
VALUES(6811, 'It''s not the place you left, you', 211, 1, 15);
VALUES(6812, 'Neither am I.', 211, 25, 15);
VALUES(6813, 'Always good value. I''ll miss her.', 211, 2, 15);
VALUES(6814, 'What d''you think?', 211, 2, 15);
VALUES(6815, 'Wouldn''t know you if I didn''t know you.', 211, 1, 15);
VALUES(6816, 'You want to tell me what that is?', 211, 2, 15);
VALUES(6817, 'Sirius gave it to me. He had a matching piece. He said if I ever needed him, all I had to do was look into it.', 211, 1, 15);
VALUES(6818, 'You mean he could see you?', 211, 2, 15);
VALUES(6819, 'Something like that. I don''t know. He died before I ever got to use it. The thing is...', 211, 1, 15);
VALUES(6820, 'Go on.', 211, 2, 15);
VALUES(6821, 'You''ll think I''m mental, but more than once, when I''ve looked into it -- I think I''ve seen Dumbledore.', 211, 1, 15);
VALUES(6822, 'Bloody hell... that''s a sight.', 211, 2, 15);
VALUES(6823, 'Well, how do I look?', 211, 22, 15);
VALUES(6824, 'Hideous.', 211, 2, 15);
VALUES(6825, 'Oh dear, I missed a spot, didn''t I? Hold still...', 211, 22, 15);
VALUES(6826, 'Couldn''t do anything about that bit in the back that''s always flipping up, could you? Dead annoying --', 211, 2, 15);
VALUES(6827, 'Never mind. I''m good.  That is you in there, isn''t it?', 211, 2, 15);
VALUES(6828, 'You can give that to Hermione to hold, all right, Griphook?', 211, 1, 15);
VALUES(6829, 'Madam Lestrange.', 212, 130, 2);
VALUES(6830, 'Good morning? Good morning? You''re Bellatrix Lestrange, not some dewy-eyed schoolgirl!', 212, 30, 2);
VALUES(6831, 'Hey. Easy.', 212, 2, 2);
VALUES(6832, 'She gives us away and we might as well use that sword to slit our own throats. Understand?', 212, 30, 2);
VALUES(6833, 'He''s right. I was being stupid.', 212, 3, 2);
VALUES(6834, 'C''mon. Let''s do it.', 212, 1, 2);
VALUES(6835, 'Identification.', 212, 130, 2);
VALUES(6836, 'I wish to enter my vault.', 212, 22, 2);
VALUES(6837, 'I see. Very well. Excuse me, won''t you?', 212, 130, 2);
VALUES(6838, 'I don''t like to be kept waiting.', 212, 22, 2);
VALUES(6839, 'Next.', 212, 130, 2);
VALUES(6840, 'He''s with me.', 212, 22, 2);
VALUES(6841, 'They know!', 212, 30, 2);
VALUES(6842, 'What do you mean?', 212, 2, 2);
VALUES(6843, 'They know she''s an imposter! They''ve been warned!', 212, 30, 2);
VALUES(6844, 'Madam Lestrange. Would you mind presenting your wand?', 212, 64, 2);
VALUES(6845, 'And why should I do that?', 212, 22, 2);
VALUES(6846, 'Harry, what do we do? Harry...?', 212, 2, 2);
VALUES(6847, 'It''s the bank''s policy. I''m sure you understand, given the current climate --', 212, 64, 2);
VALUES(6848, 'No, I most certainly do not understand --', 212, 22, 2);
VALUES(6849, 'I''m afraid I must insist.', 212, 64, 2);
VALUES(6850, 'Imperio.', 212, 1, 2);
VALUES(6851, 'Very well, Madam Lestrange. If you will follow me.', 212, 64, 2);
VALUES(6852, 'But... Bogrod, there have been special instructions regarding the Lestrange vault.', 212, 130, 2);
VALUES(6853, 'I''m fully aware of that. I''m also aware the Lestranges are one of our oldest and most respected families.', 212, 64, 2);
VALUES(6854, 'Yes, sir, but our instructions are very specific --', 212, 130, 2);
VALUES(6855, 'Let me be specific with you, Ricbert. I''ve run this bank for forty-five years, long before anyone had even heard of a Death Eater. The day may come that they feel they can run this place better than me, but that day has not yet arrived. Am I understood!', 212, 64, 2);
VALUES(6856, 'Madam, if you will, I will escort you myself.', 212, 64, 2);
VALUES(6857, 'How long before they come after us?', 212, 1, 2);
VALUES(6858, 'What''s that? Up ahead.', 212, 2, 2);
VALUES(6859, 'I should have known --', 212, 30, 2);
VALUES(6860, 'What is that, Griphook?', 212, 1, 2);
VALUES(6861, 'Griphook! What is that!', 212, 1, 2);
VALUES(6862, 'Well done. Hey.', 212, 1, 2);
VALUES(6863, 'The Thief''s Downfall. Washes away all enchantments. Can be deadly.', 212, 30, 2);
VALUES(6864, 'You don''t say.  Just out of interest... is there any other way out of here?', 212, 2, 2);
VALUES(6865, 'No.', 212, 30, 2);
VALUES(6866, 'What the devil are you all doing down here!', 212, 64, 2);
VALUES(6867, 'We need him!', 212, 30, 2);
VALUES(6868, 'Is this your doing, Griphook? You have no rights here anymore. When you gave up your keys, you --', 212, 64, 2);
VALUES(6869, 'Imperio!', 212, 2, 2);
VALUES(6870, 'Well done.', 212, 30, 2);
VALUES(6871, 'No. It''s not possible...', 212, 2, 2);
VALUES(6872, 'Bloody hell. That''s a Welsh Green.', 212, 2, 2);
VALUES(6873, 'It looks like it''s been down here forever.', 212, 3, 2);
VALUES(6874, 'Go on.', 212, 30, 2);
VALUES(6875, 'It''s been trained to expect pain when it hears the noise.', 212, 2, 2);
VALUES(6876, 'That''s barbaric. I...', 212, 3, 2);
VALUES(6877, 'We''ll only have a few seconds. In other words... they''ll be no do-', 212, 30, 2);
VALUES(6878, 'Ready, Bogrod?', 212, 30, 2);
VALUES(6879, 'Hm? Oh. Yes. Of course.', 212, 64, 2);
VALUES(6880, 'Lumos !', 212, 1, 2);
VALUES(6881, 'Lumos !', 212, 2, 2);
VALUES(6882, 'Lumos !', 212, 3, 2);
VALUES(6883, 'Blimey...', 212, 2, 2);
VALUES(6884, 'Look.', 212, 3, 2);
VALUES(6885, 'No wonder Bellatrix thought it was real.', 212, 3, 2);
VALUES(6886, 'Is it here, Harry? Can you feel anything?', 213, 2, 2);
VALUES(6887, 'It''s hot! All eyes turn to the bowl, WOBBLING MADLY on the floor, when... it SPLITS APART and begins to MULTIPLY.', 213, 3, 2);
VALUES(6888, 'Ron, your foot!', 213, 3, 2);
VALUES(6889, 'We''ll be crushed! Hurry!', 213, 30, 2);
VALUES(6890, 'That''s it. Up there.', 213, 1, 2);
VALUES(6891, 'How''re we going to reach it?', 213, 3, 2);
VALUES(6892, 'Give me the sword! The real one.', 213, 1, 2);
VALUES(6893, 'Keep going!', 213, 2, 2);
VALUES(6894, 'Harry! Behind you!', 213, 3, 2);
VALUES(6895, 'The cup!', 213, 2, 2);
VALUES(6896, 'In here!', 213, 3, 2);
VALUES(6897, 'We have a deal, Griphook.', 213, 1, 2);
VALUES(6898, 'I said I''d get you in. I never said anything about getting you out.', 213, 30, 2);
VALUES(6899, 'Griphook! Griphook!', 213, 1, 2);
VALUES(6900, 'Thieves! Help! Thieves!', 213, 30, 2);
VALUES(6901, 'Foul little git. Least we''ve got Bogrod.', 214, 2, 2);
VALUES(6902, 'That''s unfortunate.', 214, 2, 2);
VALUES(6903, 'We can''t just stand here! Who''s got an idea?', 214, 3, 2);
VALUES(6904, 'You''re asking us? You''re the brilliant one.', 214, 2, 2);
VALUES(6905, 'I''ve got something. But it''s mad.', 214, 3, 2);
VALUES(6906, 'Relashio!', 214, 3, 2);
VALUES(6907, 'That''s your idea?', 214, 2, 2);
VALUES(6908, 'Come on!', 214, 1, 2);
VALUES(6909, 'It doesn''t realize it''s free!', 214, 3, 2);
VALUES(6910, 'That was brilliant! BRILLIANT!', 214, 2, 74);
VALUES(6911, 'Bloody hell.', 214, 2, 74);
VALUES(6912, 'We''re dropping!', 214, 1, 74);
VALUES(6913, 'I say we jump!', 214, 2, 74);
VALUES(6914, 'When?', 214, 3, 74);
VALUES(6915, 'The boy has discovered our secret, Nagini. We must find out just how much he knows. We must return to our hiding places and see if the others are safe.', 214, 9, 74);
VALUES(6916, 'He knows.', 214, 1, 74);
VALUES(6917, 'How is it you --', 214, 3, 74);
VALUES(6918, 'I saw him.', 214, 1, 74);
VALUES(6919, 'You let him in! Harry, you can''t --', 214, 3, 74);
VALUES(6920, 'I can''t always help it, Hermione!', 214, 1, 74);
VALUES(6921, 'Never mind! What did you see?', 214, 2, 74);
VALUES(6922, 'He''s angry. But he''s scared too. He''s going to make sure the other Horcruxes are safe.', 214, 1, 74);
VALUES(6923, 'What happens when he finds out four are gone?', 214, 2, 74);
VALUES(6924, 'I reckon he''ll do anything to stop us from finding the rest. There''s more: one of them''s at Hogwarts.', 214, 1, 74);
VALUES(6925, 'What?', 214, 3, 74);
VALUES(6926, 'What?', 214, 2, 74);
VALUES(6927, 'You saw it?', 214, 3, 74);
VALUES(6928, 'Tonight? But we have to plan. We have to figure out what --', 214, 3, 74);
VALUES(6929, 'Honestly, Hermione, when have any of our plans actually worked? We plan, we get there and all hell breaks loose.', 214, 1, 74);
VALUES(6930, '''Fraid he''s right. One problem: Snape''s Headmaster now. We can''t just walk in the front door.', 214, 2, 74);
VALUES(6931, 'We''ll go to Hogsmeade. To Honeydukes. Take the secret passage in the cellar.', 215, 1, 74);
VALUES(6932, 'There''s something wrong with him. In the past, I could always follow his thoughts. Now everything feels disconnected.', 215, 1, 74);
VALUES(6933, 'Maybe it''s because of the Horcruxes. Maybe he''s growing weaker. Maybe he''s dying.', 215, 2, 74);
VALUES(6934, 'No. It''s more like he''s wounded. If anything, he feels more', 215, 1, 74);
VALUES(6935, 'They were ready for us.', 215, 3, 21);
VALUES(6936, 'We know you''re here, Potter. There''s no getting away.', 215, 129, 21);
VALUES(6937, 'Perhaps you need some convincing.', 215, 129, 21);
VALUES(6938, 'What''s he mean by that?', 215, 2, 21);
VALUES(6939, 'No, you''ll give us away.', 215, 3, 21);
VALUES(6940, 'Expecto Patronum!', 215, 1, 21);
VALUES(6941, 'In here, Potter.', 216, 40, 21);
VALUES(6942, 'Did you get a look at him! Fora second I thought it was --', 216, 2, 21);
VALUES(6943, 'I know.', 216, 3, 21);
VALUES(6944, 'Harry! I can see you! In here!', 216, 3, 21);
VALUES(6945, 'You bloody fools! What were you thinking coming here? Do you have any idea how dangerous it is --', 216, 40, 21);
VALUES(6946, 'You''re Aberforth.', 216, 1, 21);
VALUES(6947, 'Dumbledore''s brother. It''s you I''ve been seeing -- here. It''s', 216, 1, 21);
VALUES(6948, 'Where''ve you left him?', 216, 40, 21);
VALUES(6949, 'He''s dead.', 216, 1, 21);
VALUES(6950, 'Sorry to hear it. I liked that elf.', 216, 40, 21);
VALUES(6951, 'Mundungus Fletcher, ''bout a year ago.', 216, 40, 21);
VALUES(6952, 'Dung had no right selling you that. It belonged to --', 216, 1, 21);
VALUES(6953, 'Sirius. Albus told me. He also told me that you''d likely be hacked off if you ever found out I had it. But ask yourself where you''d be if I didn''t.', 216, 40, 21);
VALUES(6954, 'Right then. Reckon you''re hungry. Let''s get you fed, then think of the best way to get you out of here.', 216, 40, 21);
VALUES(6955, 'Do you hear much from the others? From the Order?', 216, 3, 21);
VALUES(6956, 'The Order is finished. You-Know- Who''s won. Anyone who says otherwise is kidding themselves.', 216, 40, 21);
VALUES(6957, 'We need to get into Hogwarts. Dumbledore gave us a job to do.', 216, 1, 21);
VALUES(6958, 'Did he now? Nice job? Easy?', 216, 40, 21);
VALUES(6959, 'We''ve been hunting Horcruxes. We think the last one''s in the school. But we''ll need your help getting in.', 216, 1, 21);
VALUES(6960, 'If we can find it and kill it, then we kill him, and then we can end this war once and for all. We need to get into Hogwarts tonight.', 216, 1, 21);
VALUES(6961, 'It''s not a job my brother''s given you, it''s a suicide mission. Do yourself a favor boy. Go home. Live a little longer.', 216, 40, 21);
VALUES(6962, 'Dumbledore trusted me, to see this through.', 216, 1, 21);
VALUES(6963, 'Why should he...', 216, 1, 21);
VALUES(6964, 'Keep secrets? You tell me.', 216, 40, 21);
VALUES(6965, 'I only care about the Dumbledore I knew. I trusted him.', 216, 1, 21);
VALUES(6966, 'Did you now? And why is that?', 216, 40, 21);
VALUES(6967, 'I had no reason not to --', 216, 1, 21);
VALUES(6968, 'That''s a boy''s answer. A boy who goes chasing Horcruxes on the word of a man who won''t even tell him where to start. You''re lying. Not just to me, which doesn''t matter, but to yourself as well. That''s what a fool does.', 216, 40, 21);
VALUES(6969, 'You''re drunk.', 216, 1, 21);
VALUES(6970, 'You don''t strike me as a fool, Mr. Potter. So I''ll ask you again. There must be a reason. Why do you trust anything my brother ever said to you? Why?', 216, 40, 21);
VALUES(6971, 'You know what to do...', 216, 40, 21);
VALUES(6972, 'Where''ve you sent her?', 216, 1, 21);
VALUES(6973, 'You''ll see soon enough.', 216, 40, 21);
VALUES(6974, 'That''s Ariana, isn''t it? Your sister. She''s beautiful.', 216, 3, 21);
VALUES(6975, 'She''ll always be beautiful.', 216, 40, 21);
VALUES(6976, 'She died very young, didn''t she.', 216, 3, 21);
VALUES(6977, 'My brother sacrificed many things, Mr. Potter, in his journey to find power, including her. She was devoted to him -- he gave her everything, but time.', 216, 40, 21);
VALUES(6978, 'Mr. Dumbledore... thank you.', 216, 3, 21);
VALUES(6979, 'Did save our lives twice. Kept an eye on us in that mirror. That doesn''t seem like someone who''s given up, does it?', 216, 3, 21);
VALUES(6980, 'She''s coming back! And she''s got someone with her!', 216, 3, 21);
VALUES(6981, 'Who''s that with her? Bloody hell...', 216, 2, 21);
VALUES(6982, 'I knew you''d come! I told them alii! Harry Potter would never abandon Hogwarts!', 217, 10, 55);
VALUES(6983, 'Neville, you look...', 217, 1, 55);
VALUES(6984, 'Like hell? I reckon. This is nothing. Seamus is worse. You''ll see. Hermione! Ron!', 217, 10, 55);
VALUES(6985, 'Hey, Ab. There might be a couple more people on the way.', 217, 10, 55);
VALUES(6986, 'Well? Ready?', 217, 10, 55);
VALUES(6987, 'I don''t remember this being on the Marauder''s Map.', 217, 2, 55);
VALUES(6988, 'That''s because it never existed till now. The seven secret passages were sealed off before the start of the year. This is the only way in or out now. The grounds are crawling with Death Eaters and Dementors.', 217, 10, 55);
VALUES(6989, 'How bad is it, Neville? With Snape as Headmaster.', 217, 3, 55);
VALUES(6990, 'Hardly ever see him. It''s the Carrows you have to watch out for.', 217, 10, 55);
VALUES(6991, 'The Carrows?', 217, 1, 55);
VALUES(6992, 'Brother and sister. They''re in charge of discipline. Like punishment, the Carrows.', 217, 10, 55);
VALUES(6993, 'They did that to you? But why?', 217, 3, 55);
VALUES(6994, 'Today''s Dark Arts lesson had us practicing the Cruciatus Curse. On First Years. I refused. Hogwarts has changed.', 217, 10, 55);
VALUES(6995, 'Aw, c''mon. Don''t be grim. We''re all used to it by now. And the thing is, it helps when people stand up, gives everyone hope. I used to notice that when you did it, Harry. C''mon, we''re almost there.', 217, 10, 55);
VALUES(6996, 'Let''s have a bit of fun, shall we?  Hey! Listen up, you lot! I''ve brought you a surprise!', 217, 10, 55);
VALUES(6997, 'Blimey.', 217, 29, 55);
VALUES(6998, 'Get the word out to Remus and the others that Harry''s back.', 217, 10, 55);
VALUES(6999, 'River, DA calling. Do you read? We have a new weather report: Lightning has struck. I repeat, lightning has struck...', 217, 111, 55);
VALUES(7000, 'Okay, okay! Stand down! lLet''s not kill them before You-Know-Who gets the chance!', 217, 10, 55);
VALUES(7074, 'If you''re to find her, you''ll find her down there.', 221, 25, 53);
VALUES(7001, 'Okay. There''s something we need to find, something hidden here in the castle. It could help us defeat You-Know-Who.', 217, 1, 55);
VALUES(7002, 'What is it?', 217, 10, 55);
VALUES(7003, 'We don''t know.', 217, 1, 55);
VALUES(7004, 'Where is it?', 217, 75, 55);
VALUES(7005, 'I realize it''s not much to go on.', 217, 1, 55);
VALUES(7006, 'That''s nothing to go on.', 217, 29, 55);
VALUES(7007, 'I think it might have something to do with Ravenclaw. It would be small, easy to conceal, valuable. Any ideas?', 217, 1, 55);
VALUES(7008, 'Well, there''s Rowena Ravenclaw''s lost diadem.', 217, 25, 55);
VALUES(7009, 'The lost diadem of Ravenclaw? Hasn''t anyone ever heard of it? It''s quite famous.', 217, 25, 55);
VALUES(7010, 'Yes, but Luna, it''s lost. For centuries now. There''s not a person alive today who''s seen it.', 217, 55, 55);
VALUES(7011, 'Excuse me. But would someone tell me: what''s a bloody diadem?', 217, 2, 55);
VALUES(7012, 'It''s a kind of crown. You know, like a tiara.', 217, 55, 55);
VALUES(7013, 'Ravenclaw''s was rumored to have magical properties, to enhance the wisdom of the wearer.', 217, 55, 55);
VALUES(7014, 'Harry.', 217, 20, 55);
VALUES(7015, 'Hey there. Ron smiles, about to speak, then notices Ginny''s eyes have not left Harry. He frowns, speaks to Hermione.', 217, 1, 55);
VALUES(7016, 'Six months she hasn''t seen me and it''s like I''m Frankie First Year. I mean, I''m only her brother.', 217, 2, 55);
VALUES(7017, 'Got loads of those, though, doesn''t she? There''s only one Harry.', 217, 29, 55);
VALUES(7018, 'Shut up, Seamus.', 217, 2, 55);
VALUES(7019, 'What is it, Ginny?', 217, 10, 55);
VALUES(7020, 'Snape knows. He knows that Harry was spotted in Hogsmeade.', 217, 20, 55);
